label: anatomical axis
Defs: A straight line through space, intersecting an anatomical entity.

label: anatomical side
Defs: An anatomical region bounded by a plane perpendicular to an axis through the middle.

label: anatomical entity
Defs: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: anatomical plane
Defs: A flat 2D plane intersecting an anatomical continuant, dividing it into two adjacent portions.

label: anatomical surface
Defs: A 2D surface of an anatomical continuant.

label: left side
Defs: The side of an organism that is left of the sagittal plane.

label: right side
Defs: The side of an organism that is right of the sagittal plane.

label: left-right axis
Defs: An axis that bisects an organism from left to right sides of body, through a sagittal plane.

label: upper side
Defs: na

label: upper-lower axis
Defs: An anatomical axis determined by gravity.

label: lower side
Defs: na

Defs: na

label: deep side
Defs: na

label: superficial side
Defs: na

label: deep-superficial axis
Defs: An axis that extends from an internal position to a more external position in the body or body part.

label: anatomical boundary
Defs: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

label: anatomical margin
Defs: Fiat anatomical region extending a short distance from the boundary of an object inwards.

label: anatomical region
Defs: A 3D region in space without well-defined compartmental boundaries; for example, the dorsal region of an ectoderm.

label: parasagittal plane
Defs: Sagittal plane that divides a bilateral body into unequal left and right parts.

label: sagittal plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size.

label: midsagittal plane
Defs: Sagittal plane that divides bilateral body into equal left and right parts.

label: anatomical line CARO
Defs: A one dimensional, immaterial anatomical entity.

label: anterior-posterior axis
Defs: An axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: transverse plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides body into anterior and posterior parts.

label: dorsal-ventral axis
Defs: An axis that is approximately perpendicular to the anterior-posterior axis and that extends through the horizontal plane of the body.

label: apical-basal axis relative to substrate
Defs: An axis that extends through an organism or organism part from the part of the organism or organism part attached to a substrate (basal) to the furthest from the attachment (apical). Note that the apical-basal axis is often used for organismal parts where there is attachment via a basal lamina or other structure.

label: proximal-distal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the point of attachment of a structure (proximal) to the  point furthest away from the plane of attachment (distal).

label: horizontal plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides bilateral body into dorsal and ventral parts.

label: upper-lower gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the upper-lower axis.

label: anatomical gradient
Defs: Material anatomical entity defined by change in the value of some quantity per unit of distance across some spatial axis.

label: deep-superficial gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the deep-superficial axis.

label: superior side
Defs: The side that is higher relative to the substrate.

label: apical-basal gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the apical-basal axis.

label: proximal-distal gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the proximal-distal axis.

label: inferior side
Defs: The side that is lower relative to the substrate.

label: antero-dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and dorsal regions of a body or body part.

label: anterior side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure anterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: dorsal side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: anterior region
Defs: Anatomical region anteriorly located on the body or body part.

label: dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region dorsally located on the body or body part.

label: antero-ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: ventral side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure ventral to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same horizontal plane.

label: ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region ventrally located on the body or body part.

label: postero-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and lateral regions of the body or body part.

label: posterior side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure posterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: adaxial-abaxial axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that extends from the side of the anatomical entity that is closer to an axis (adaxial) to the side that is further from the same axis (abaxial).

label: medial-external axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that extends from the center of the body outwards or externally.

label: medial-radial axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that is perpendicular to an apical/basal axis or proximal/distal axis and extends from the center of an axis (shoot axis or root in the case of plants) to any point on the exterior of the axis.

label: oral-aboral axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the oral opening to the furthest point in an organism that is directly opposite.

label: animal-vegetal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the animal end of an egg or early embryo to the opposite, vegetal end. In animals with yolk-bearing eggs, the vegetal end is the yolk bearing pole. (pertains to animals only - both vertebrate and invertebrate embryos).

label: apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth
Defs: An axis of a plant structure that is determined by the direction of apical growth, either by an apical meristem or an apical cell. Apical is toward the direction of apical growth: toward the tip of a growing shoot axis, root, thallus, or non-vascular leaf. Basal is away from the direction of apical growth: toward the root-shoot junction in the case of the primary root or stem, toward the primary root or stem for higher order roots or branches, toward the point of attachment for non-vascular leaves, and toward the original point of growth (as determined in the embryo) for thalli.

label: tangential plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that is perpendicular to a radial plane.

label: radial plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that follows the two dimensions specified by an apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth and a medial-lateral axis.

label: anterior to
Defs: x anterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: posterior to
Defs: x posterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the body/tail. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: distal to
Defs: x distal to y iff x is further along the proximo-distal axis than y, towards the appendage tip. A proximo-distal axis extends from tip of an appendage (distal) to where it joins the body (proximal).

label: proximal to
Defs: x proximal to y iff x is closer to the point of attachment with the body than y.

label: dorsal to
Defs: x dorsal to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: ventral to
Defs: x ventral to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: obsolete surrounds
Defs: na

label: vicinity of
Defs: na

label: approximately perpendicular to
Defs: Crosses at an angle that is 90 degrees, or close to 90 degrees. In any non-linear organism, the main axes are rarely perpendicular when taken through the organism as a whole.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: On the same side as. For example, the left arm is ipsilateral to the left leg.

label: in lateral side of
Defs: X in lateral side of Y <=> if X is in left side of Y or X is in right side of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: contralateral to
Defs: On the opposite side from. For example, the left arm is contralateral to the right arm (and the right leg).

label: deep to
Defs: Further away from the surface of the organism. Thus, the muscular layer is deep to the skin, but superficial to the intestines.

label: superficial to
Defs: Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

label: obsolete surrounded_by
Defs: na

label: left of
Defs: Closer to the left side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is left of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: right of
Defs: Closer to the right side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is right of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: opposite to
Defs: Direcly opposite to. i.e. on the opposite side through the axis.

label: in left side of
Defs: X in left side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the left portion.

label: in right side of
Defs: X in right side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the right portion.

label: in posterior side of
Defs: X posterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the posterior portion.

label: in anterior side of
Defs: X anterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the anterior portion.

label: in proximal side of
Defs: x in proximal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the proximal portion.

label: in distal side of
Defs: x in distal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the distal portion.

label: in superficial part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the superficial portion.

label: in deep part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the deep portion.

label: proximalmost part of
Defs: X proximalmost part of Y <=> X is in proximal side of Y and X is adjacent to the proximal boundary of Y

label: immediately deep to
Defs: x immediately deep to y iff x deep_to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: immediately superficial to
Defs: x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: distalmost part of
Defs: X distalmost part of Y <=> X is in distal side of Y and X is adjacent to the distal boundary of Y

Defs: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

label: color hue
Defs: A chromatic scalar-circular quality inhering in an object that manifests in an observer by virtue of the dominant wavelength of the visible light; may be subject to fiat divisions, typically into 7 or 8 spectra.

label: chromatic property

label: luminous flux
Defs: A scalar optical quality which obtains by the magnitude of the light emitted by the bearer.

label: color pattern
Defs: A chromatic property that is the relative position of different hues or degrees of saturation.

label: spatial pattern

label: parallelogram
Defs:
A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:
1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.
2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.
3. The diagonals bisect each other.
4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.
5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)
6.It possesses rotational symmetry.
7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.
8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

label: ploidy
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s number of homologous sets of chromosomes in the nucleus or primary chromosome-containing compartment of the cell, each set essentially coding for all the biological traits of the organism.

label: cellular quality
Defs: A monadic quality of continuant that exists at the cellular level of organisation.

label: haploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a single set of homologous chromosomes.

label: euploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing an integral multiple of the monoploid number, possibly excluding the sex-determining chromosomes.

label: monoploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a single set of unique homologous chromosomes.

label: polyploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing more than two homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: autopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing chromosomes derived from a single species.

label: allopolyploidy
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing chromosomes derived from different species.

label: paleopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an ancient polyploid ancestor.

label: triploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing three homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: tetraploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing four homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: pentaploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing five homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: hexaploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing four homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: aneuploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a non-integral multiple of the monoploid number, due to extra or missing chromosomes.

label: monosomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing only one chromosome from a pair in a cell\'s nucleus.

label: disomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing only two chromosome from a pair in a cell\'s nucleus.

label: uniparental disomy
Defs: A disomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing two copies of the chromosome from one of the parents (with no contribution from the other parent).

label: trisomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing three, instead of two, chromosomes of a particular numbered type in an organism.

label: partial trisomy
Defs: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer when part of the bearer\'s extra chromosome is attached to one of the other chromosomes, or if one of the bearer\'s chromosomes has two copies of part of its chromosome.

label: mosaic trisomy
Defs: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having extra chromosomal material in only some of it\'s cells.

label: endopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s chromosome number being increased by endomitosis and for which the degree of ploidy is proportional to the number of times that endomitosis has taken place.

label: diploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two copies (homologs) of each chromosome, usually one from the mother and one from the father.

label: haplodiploid
Defs: A diploidy quality inhering in a bearer in by virtue of belonging in a species whose one of the sexes has haploid cells and the other has diploid cells.

label: cellular potency
Defs: A cellular quality that arises by virtue of whether the bearer\'s disposition to differentiate into one or more mature cell types.

label: self-renewal
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the ability to go through numerous cycles of cell division while maintaining the undifferentiated state.

label: proliferative
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a cell that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to grow and proliferate in number through cell division.

label: totipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers and extraembryonic cell types.

label: unipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce only one differentiated cell type.

label: oligopotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types of a specific lineage and lack self renewing capacity.

label: multipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types.

label: pluripotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers but not extraembryonic cell types.

label: nucleate quality
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s number of nuclei.

label: anucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having no nucleus.

label: binucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two nuclei.

label: multinucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having more than one nucleus.

label: mononucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one nucleus.

label: nucleated
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one or more nucleus.

label: ciliatedness
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having thin, tail-like projections extending outwards from the cell body.

label: buoyancy
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air.

label: osmolality
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of osmoles of solute per kilogram of solvent.

label: decreased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively low.

label: increased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively high.

label: specificity to
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability of a probe to react precisely with a specific target molecule.

label: upturned
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved or tilted such that the tip points upwards.

label: forward scatter
Defs: A reflectivity quality inhering in light by virtue of the bearer\'s scattering occurring at small angle to the incident beam.

label: side scatter
Defs: A reflective quality that is the light scattering occurring at wide angle (around 90 degrees) to the incident beam.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being on the same side in relation to another structure.

label: axial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located towards the central axis of the organism or an extremity.

label: biconcave
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s curving inward on both sides or surfaces.

label: biconvex
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being convex on both sides or surface.

label: anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: A diameter that is along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: decreased anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively small.

label: increased anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively large.

label: trapezoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a quadrilateral with two parallel sides.

label: dendritic
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having smaller branches arising from larger branches. Resembling a tree in branching structure.

label: abaxial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being away from or on the opposite side of the central axis.

label: adaxial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on the side nearest to the axis of an organ or organism.

label: mosaicism
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more cell populations that differ in genetic makeup. This situation can affect any type of cell, including blood cells, gametes (egg and sperm cells), and skin.

label: lateral and rotional curvature
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved around an axis and towards the side.

label: increased occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively high.

label: dorso-ventrally flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along dorso-ventral axis.

label: laterally compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along transverse axis.

label: increased fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively high.

label: decreased fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively low.

label: increased area
Defs: An area which is relatively high.

label: decreased area
Defs: An area which is relatively low.

label: emmision wavelength
Defs: The specific wavelength of light emitted by a fluorescent molecule, such as a labelled probe, upon absorption of light at the (higher) excitation wavelength.

label: absorption wavelength
Defs: The specific wavelength of radiation that can be retained by a bearer.

label: na
Defs: na

label: columnar
Defs: A shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being elongated and cylindrical.

label: fenestrated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delimited by a surface with holes.

label: star shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being arranged like rays or radii; radiating from a common center.

label: crystal configuration
Defs: A solid configuration inhering in a material entity by virtue of its constituent atoms, molecules, or ions being arranged in an orderly repeating pattern extending in all three spatial dimensions.

label: stratification
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s layered configuration.

label: stratified
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a layered configuration.

label: unstratified
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a layered configuration.

label: affinity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the molecular attraction exerted between two atoms or compounds.

label: increased affinity
Defs: An affinity which is relatively high.

label: decreased affinity
Defs: An affinity which is relatively low.

label: avidity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the synergistic strength of bond affinities between multiple bond interactions.

label: increased avidity
Defs: An avidity which is relatively high.

label: decreased avidity
Defs: An avidity which is relatively low.

label: stacked
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned with multiple entities of the same type above and below.

label: hollow
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an empty space or cavity within.

label: na
Defs: na

label: broken into two pieces
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being seperated into two contiguous wholes.

label: shattered
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being broken into multiple contiguous wholes.

label: partially broken
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being still one contiguous whole but structurally damaged such that in danger of become two or more.

label: obsolete post-mortem
Defs: The period after death of the organism.

label: obsolete pre-mortem
Defs: The period before death of the organism.

label: na
Defs: na

label: bullet-shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being short and wide and tapered distally.

label: monocystic
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s body consisting of one sac.

label: polycystic
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s body containing more than one cyst - formations of an epithelium bounded cavity not associated with neoplasia.

label: adenomatous
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a glandular epithelial cell.

label: subacute
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an onset and time course between acute and chronic.

label: anaplastic
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a neoplastic cell by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting breakdown of cell-cell interaction maintaining tissue architecture, proliferative dysregulation and bizarre modification to nucleus size and shape.

label: ballooning
Defs: A volume quality inhering in a degenerating cell by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting an increase in volume associated with cytoplasmic abnormalities.

label: basophilic
Defs: An affinity inhering in a tissue constituent by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific ph conditions.

label: obsolete neoplasm disposition
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour to progress or fail to progress during it\'s life time.

label: neoplastic, non-malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: neoplastic, malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: neoplastic, metastatic
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spread and invade distant tissues.

label: neoplastic, invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to invade surrounding tissues.

label: neoplastic, non-invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to invade surrounding tissues.

label: differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its stable specialization to a particular cell type.

label: undifferentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having not yet acquired a special structure of function.

label: metaplastic
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having changed from one fully differentiated state into another.

label: infiltrative
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s penetrating or permeating another substance or area.

label: inflamed
Defs: A compositional quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s infiltration by leukocytes, local edema and accumulation of plasma proteins.

label: hemorrhagic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting excessive discharge of blood from the blood vessels.

label: poorly differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its lacking most of the cellular characteristics which would allow it to be fully differentiated.

label: peripheral
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the edge or boundary of a related entity.

label: papillary
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling small nipple like projection.

label: caseous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling cheese.

label: well differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its having most of the cellular characteristics of the tissue of origin.

label: moderately well differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its lacking few of the cellular characteristics which would allow it to be fully differentiated.

label: cribriform
Defs: Perforated like a sieve.

label: fatty
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing excess lipid.

label: fibrinoid
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing fibrin.

label: fibrinopurulent
Defs: A composition quality inhering in exudate by virtue of the bearer\'s containing fibrin.

label: glandular
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a gland.

label: multiple
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in more than two copies.

label: hydropic
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of intracellular fluid.

label: suppurative
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to generate pus.

label: trabecular
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s structureresembling an irregular meshwork with cross-linking struts.

label: mixed
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being composed of more than one identifiable entities.

label: minimal
Defs: Being smallest in amount, extent or degree.

label: laminar
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

label: nodular
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting a knot-like mass.

label: osseous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing bone.

label: scirrhous
Defs: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure and fibrous.

label: serous
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing or resembling serum.

label: neoplastic, deeply invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to invade surrounding tissues to a large extend.

label: abduction
Defs: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer\'s movement away from the medial plane of the body.

label: displaced to
Defs: An angular placement quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being changed in position in relation to another entity.

label: adduction
Defs: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer\'s movement closer the medial plane of the body.

label: fibrillary
Defs: A composition quaity inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing of or pertaining to fibrils, or nanoscale fibers.

label: delayed closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delay to complete the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: radiopacity
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s relative inability of electromagnetism to pass through a particular material, particularly X-rays.

label: radiopaque
Defs: A readiopacity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s prevention of the passage of electromagnetic radiation.

label: edibility
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be eaten.

label: edible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as food.

label: inedible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.

label: irregular density
Defs: A density quality which lacks pattern.

label: bracket
Defs: na

label: sloped downward
Defs: na

label: increased radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity that is relatively high.

label: decreased radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity that is relatively low.

label: virulence
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the severity of infectious disease caused by the bearer in a target organism.

label: reduced virulence
Defs: A virulence that is relatively low.

label: increased virulence
Defs: A virulence that is relatively high.

label: ivory
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting increased density resulting in exhibiting increased degree of radiopacity (in X-rays).

label: splayed caudal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the part of the body from which the tail arises.

label: splayed dorsal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the back or upper surface of an organism.

label: splayed lateral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the side.

label: splayed rostral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards the front of an organism.

label: splayed ventral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards the abdomen of an organism.

label: medially rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the middle of an organism.

label: laterally rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the side of an organism.

label: partially dislocated
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being slightly out of its usual or proper place, or position.

Defs: na

label: na

label: bicornuate
Defs: Having two horns or horn-shaped branches.

label: high-arched
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming or resembling an arch of an increased apical height.

label: herniated into
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded through an abnormal opening in the wall that contains it into the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: curved medial
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the middle.

label: drooping
Defs: To bent or hang downwards.

label: premature closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s premature completion of the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: herniated out of
Defs: A protruding quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded out of the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: split medially
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split along the median axis.

label: split laterally
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split asymmetrically on one side.

label: split bilaterally
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split on two side.

label: split radially
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split along the radial axis.

label: misaligned towards
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a improper spatial positioning towards an additional entity.

label: misaligned away from
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a improper spatial positioning away from an additional entity.

label: deviation
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards another entity.

label: deviation towards the lateral side
Defs: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards the side.

label: deviation towards the medial side
Defs: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards the middle.

label: mislocalised radially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being out of its usual or proper place, or position around a central point or axis.

label: mislocalised proximally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards to point of attachment or origin.

label: straight
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being free of curves, bends, or angles.

label: cyclicity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether that there is a presence of cycles in the connection of the atoms within the molecular entity.

label: cyclic cyclicity
Defs: Cyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms of the molecule do contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through bonds).

label: acyclic cyclicity
Defs: Acyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms within the molecule do not contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through the bonds).

label: polarity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether or not the molecular entity has a separation of electric charge which leads to the molecule having an electric dipole.

label: polar polarity
Defs: Polar polarity is a quality that inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity is polar, i.e. does possess an electric dipole.

label: nonpolar polarity
Defs: A molecular quality which inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity does not possess an electrical dipole.

label: electric polarizability
Defs: The ease of distortion of the electron cloud of a molecular entity by an electric field.

label: aromaticity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the presence of a conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

label: aromatic
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity when it possesses at least one ring that is aromatic, i.e. A conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

label: non-aromatic
Defs: A quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecule possessing no rings that are aromatic.

label: electric charge
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the overall electric charge of the molecule, which is due to a comparison between the total number of electrons and the total number of protons.

label: neutral charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing the same amount of electrons overall as protons, thus having an overall neutral charge.

label: positive charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more protons overall than electrons, thus having an overall positive charge.

label: negative charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more electrons overall than protons, thus having an overall negative charge.

label: electronegativity
Defs: A quality that describes the power of an atom to attract electrons to itself .

label: meltability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed from a solid to a liquid state especially by the application of heat.

label: vaporizability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed into a gaseous state.

label: handedness
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

label: left handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: right handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: ambidextrous handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: capacitance
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to hold an electrical charge.

label: neonatal
Defs: A maturity quality inhering to a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the point or short after birth.

label: insertion depth
Defs: A quality that is the distance between the end of the inserted object and the surface of the object into which it penetrates.

label: spoon-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of a spoon.

label: incisiform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of an incisor tooth.

label: bulbous
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a teardrop.

label: recurved
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved backward or inward.

label: slender
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being small or narrow in circumference or width in proportion to length or height.

label: obclavate
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape being inversely clavate.

label: bilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having two lobes.

label: falciform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of a scythe or sickle.

label: ubiquinated
Defs: A molecular quality that pertains to the post-translational modification of a protein by the covalent attachment of one or more ubiquitin monomer.

label: nitrated
Defs: A molecular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being combined, or impregnated, with nitric acid, or some of its compounds.

label: demyelinated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s loss of myelin sheath.

label: fan-shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer that is shaped in the form of a fan.

label: phosphorylated
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer\'s having a phosphate (PO4) group.

label: phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the addition of a phosphate (PO4) group to the bearer.

label: dephosphorylated
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a phosphate (PO4) group.

label: increased phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a more than normal extent, or fully saturated with phosphate groups.

label: decreased phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a lesser than normal extent, or less than fully.

label: oxidized
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having reacted with oxygen, or been modified by oxidation (the reaction in which the atoms of an element lose electrons and the valence of the element increases).

label: V-shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter V.

label: L-shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter L.

label: subcylindrical
Defs: A cylindrical shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being imperfectly cylindrical or approximately cylindrical.

label: cup-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape form resembling the shape of a cup.

label: acuminate
Defs: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s tapering gradually to a sharp point.

label: subrectangular
Defs: A quadrangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being approximately rectangular.

label: subtriangular
Defs: A triangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, triangular.

label: multifid
Defs: A split shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or being divided into many lobes or similar segments.

label: semicircular
Defs: A 2-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having shape or form of half a circle.

label: far from
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located far (not close to) in space in relation to another entity.

label: emarginate
Defs: A notched shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a notched tip or edge.

label: blade-like
Defs: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flat, slender, and tapering to a point.

label: aliform
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a wing.

label: retrorse
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved backward or downward.

label: antrorse
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved forward or upward.

label: hourglass-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s nearly) symmetric shape wide at its ends and narrow in the middle, resembling the figure of number 8.

label: teardrop-shaped
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling falling drop.

label: trilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having three lobes.

label: mass flow rate
Defs: A flow rate quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the mass of substance which passes through a given surface per unit time.

label: degree of pigmentation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or lacking of substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: pigmented
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: unpigmented
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: increased pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality that is relatively high.

label: decreased pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality that is relative low.

label: antero-posteriorly flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along the antero-posterior axis.

label: platelike
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

label: tricuspidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing three cusps.

label: multicuspidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing more than one cusp.

label: pointed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a point.

label: semi erect
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being partially upright in position or posture.

label: located in
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location within another entity.

label: centered
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located in a position equidistant from edges.

label: accumulation
Defs: A structural quality of the collection or massing of one physical object within another physical object.

label: increased accumulation
Defs: An increased number of physical objects that are accumulated within another physical object usually as a result of a failure to break down or remove objects in a timely manner.

label: decreased accumulation
Defs: An accumulation which is relative low.

label: parallel to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at the same continuous distance relative to another object.

label: marbled
Defs: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being colored with a variegated pattern resembling marble,.

label: mottled
Defs: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being dappled with spots, patches, or blotches of different colors.

label: high contrast color pattern
Defs: A color pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s color pattern in which light and dark colors (for example white and black) are codistributed to create a visual impression.

label: barred
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s exhibiting vertical bars of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

label: iridescent
Defs: A quality of certain surfaces which appear to change colour as the angle of view changes.

label: articulated with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s participating in a joint with another entity.

Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a short and stout cylindrical shape.

label: boomerang shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a boomerang, with two arms connected at an angle.

label: subovoid
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a shape not quite ovoid. approximately ovoid.

label: concavo-convex
Defs: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer being concave on one side and convex on the other.

label: ring shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a ring (a circular shape enclosing a space).

label: spur shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a small, spike-like shape.

label: homeostatic
Defs: Pertaining to the ability or tendency of an organism or cell to maintain internal equilibrium by adjusting its physiological processes.

label: borderline intensity
Defs: An intensity which is borderline in it its effect or force as compared to baseline or normal.

label: profound intensity
Defs: An intensity which is characterized by being very severe.

label: episodic
Defs: An occurrence quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a course that occurs occasionally.

label: refractory
Defs: An occurrence of a process during which time there is an inability to change the course, extent, or repetition of the process.

label: secondary
Defs: A quality in which the effect or outcome is not primary or the focus of the observation.

label: hemispheroid
Defs: A 3-D shape that is half of a sphere.

label: variability of count
Defs: A variability quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer having a variable number or count of an entity.

label: pear shaped
Defs: Having the shape of a pear; tapering near the top and bulging toward the base or bottom. From thefreedictionary.com

label: paddle shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling the form of a paddle.

label: subelliptical
Defs: A shape that is almost an ellipse.

label: radiating
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer expanding outward, or having parts expanding outward, from a center point.

label: differentiated from
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being morphologically distinguishable from another entity.

label: hypsodont
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having dentition characterized by high-crowned teeth and enamel which extends far past the gum line, which provides extra material for wear and tear.

label: brachydont
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having dentition characterized by low-crowned teeth. Human teeth are brachydont.

label: molariform
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an entity in the form of a molar tooth.

label: plumose
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many fine filaments or branches that give a feathery appearance: for example, resembling a feather.

label: continuous with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing an uninterrupted or unbroken connection or spatial distribution relative to the position of another entity.

label: complete structure
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being fully formed compared to entities lacking parts.

label: incomplete structure
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking parts or having a reduced form compared to fully formed entities.

label: subspherical
Defs: A spheroid shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, spherical.

label: tapered size
Defs: A size quality inhering in an entity or set of entities in which size increases or decreases along the extent of the entity or set.

label: surrounded by
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being enclosed on all sides by another entity.

label: labiolingually compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being compressed from the side facing the lips to the side facing the tongue.

label: mesiodistally compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being compressed from the side facing the midline of the jaw to the side opposite the midline.

label: curved lingually
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the tongue.

label: irregularly shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering on a bearer by virtue of a bearer\'s shape lacking in pattern or uniformity; for example, it may have sides of different lengths, different curvatures, or unequal angles.

label: unicuspidate
Defs: Cuspidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a single cusp.

label: uniform diameter
Defs: A diameter that remains constant throughout the extent of an entity.

label: parasagittal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane.

label: longitudinal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed along the longitudinal or anterior-posterior axis.

label: maximally connected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of a single, maximally connected structure.

label: disconnected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.

label: propagation velocity
Defs: The velocity of spatial propagation of a process. Examples include the velocity of propagation of an action potential along an axon.

label: increased propagation velocity
Defs: A propagation velocity that is higher than normal.

label: decreased propagation velocity
Defs: A propagation velocity that is lower than normal.

label: spatial distribution of a process
Defs: A physical quality of a process that is its spatial distribution.  For example, bone mineralization follows stereotypical spatial distribution patterns during development, which may be altered in some phenotypes.

label: absence due to degeneration
Defs: Absence due to a degenerative process.

label: process efficacy
Defs: The ability of a process to produce its output.

label: decreased efficacy
Defs: A decrease in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: increased efficacy
Defs: A increase in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: tendrilous
Defs: Slender and spirally coiled.

label: polymeric
Defs: A quality inhering in a structure by virtue of it consisting of many of repeated, similar or identical subunits, arranged in some orderly array.

label: humidity
Defs: A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer\'s water vapour content.

label: increased humidity
Defs: An increase in humidity.

label: decreased humidity
Defs: An decrease in humidity.

label: quality of a plasma
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of roughly equal proportions of positively and negatively charged particles, having neither a defined volume nor defined shape, having internal magnetic fields, and being electrically conductive.

label: degree of illumination
Defs: The degree to which the bearer is exposed to visible light.

label: increased degree of illumination
Defs: An increase in illumination.

label: decreased degree of illumination
Defs: An decrease in illumination.

label: stepped
Defs: Having a shape or form that resembles a step of a stairway (e.g., a ledge or offset margin).

label: quality of a colloid
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of a portion of the bearer\'s molecular or polymolecular constituents present in one phase being dispersed in a portion of the bearer\'s constituents present in another phase.

label: quality of an aerosol
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being suspended in a gas.

label: C-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter C.

label: J-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter J.

label: combustibility
Defs: The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.

label: increased combustibility
Defs: An increase in combustibility.

label: decreased combustibility
Defs: An decrease in combustibility.

label: increased porosity
Defs: An increase in porosity.

label: decreased porosity
Defs: An decrease in porosity.

label: stability
Defs: quality, state, or degree of being stable.

label: increased stability
Defs: An increase in stability.

label: decreased stability

label: quality of a suspension
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being transiently dispersed in a solid, liquid, or gas before settling due to gravity or centrifugal forces.

label: plume-shaped
Defs: A shape that ineres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s mass being distributed in a feather-like fashion.

label: genotypic sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual based upon genotypic composition of sex chromosomes.

label: male genotypic sex

label: female genotypic sex

label: potability
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be used as a safe means of hydration.

label: non-potable

label: potable
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.

label: partially anterioralized

label: partially dorsalized

label: partially posterioralized

label: partially ventralized

label: heterotaxic

label: originates from

label: pathogenicity

label: plush

label: posteroventral orientation

label: fringed

label: dorsomedial orientation

label: band shaped

label: trough shaped

label: pentagonal

label: fibrotic

label: spayed female

label: lesioned

label: cardinal direction
Defs: The four cardinal directions or cardinal points are the directions north, east, south, and west, commonly denoted by their initials, N, E, S, W. East and west are at right angles to north and south, with east being in the clockwise direction of rotation from north and west being directly opposite east.

label: north
Defs: North is one of the four compass points or cardinal directions. It is the opposite of south and is perpendicular to east and west.

label: south
Defs: South is one of the four cardinal directions or compass points. South is the polar opposite of north and is perpendicular to east and west.

label: east
Defs: East is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from west.

label: west
Defs: West is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from east.

label: decreased spatial extent of a process
Defs: A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a smaller length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.

label: increased spatial extent of a process
Defs: A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a greater length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.

label: decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) < magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: different_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: directly_associated_with
Defs: q1 directly_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

Defs: The wing membrane that is delimited by wing veins.

label: arolium
Defs: The lobe that is connected proximodorsally with the manubrium and proximoventrally with the planta.

label: lobe
Defs: The evagination that is mostly membranous.

label: pretarsus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is apical to the telotarsus and composed of the empodium, auxilia, planta, pulvillum, unguis, unguitractor plate, auxiliar sclerite and manubrium.

label: articular line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends on the border between two articulating sclerites.

label: articular process
Defs: The projection that bears the articular surface.

label: articulation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of two adjacent articular surfaces.

label: aulax
Defs: The impression that is on the first valvifer-first valvula complex accommodates the rhachis.

label: olistheter
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the rhachis of the second valvula and the aulax of the first valvula.

label: dorsal ramus of the first valvula
Defs: The region that extends along the dorsal margin of the first valvula and bears the aulax.

label: auxilia
Defs: na

label: auxiliar sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located between the unguitractor and the bases of claws.

label: axilla
Defs: The area that is located posterior to the transscutal articulation and anterior to the scutoscutellar suture.

label: mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly of the transscutal line and is composed of the axillae and the mesoscutellum.

label: axillar carina
Defs: The line that separates the dorsal and lateral axillar surfaces.

label: axillary cord
Defs: The area that is heavily sclerotized and located proximally on the posterior wing margin.

label: wing base
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the pteralia, humeral complex, tegula and axillary cord.

label: axillary region
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the axillary sclerites.

label: pteralia
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the axillary sclerites and the humeral plate.

label: axillary sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the axillary region and articulates with one of the thoracic wing processes.

label: axillula
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the mesoscutellum and is limited anteriorly by the scutoscutellar suture and medially by the axillular line.

label: mesoscutellum
Defs: The scutellum that is located on the mesonotum.

label: axillular carina
Defs: The axillular line that is a carina.

label: axillular line
Defs: The line that is sublateral, and extends between the medial end of the mesoscutellar arm and the scutoscutellar suture.

label: axillular setae
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the median margin of axillula.

label: row of setae
Defs: The row that is composed of setae.

label: band
Defs: The area that is oblong and differs from surrounding areas in coloration, surface sculpture and setae.

label: bar
Defs: The process that is linear and wider proximally than distally.

label: basal bridge
Defs: The area that connects the parosicculi.

label: parossiculus
Defs: The sclerite that is connected via conjunctiva distomedially to the gonostipes, and articulates with the gonossiculus.

label: basal grooves
Defs: The row of impressions that extends along the anterior margin of an abdominal tergum or a sternum.

label: row of impressions
Defs: The row that is composed of impressions.

label: syntergum
Defs: The sclerite that is composed of fused abdominal terga.

label: basal hooklets
Defs: na

label: gonostipes/volsella complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is part of the gonostyle/volsella complex and is composed of the sclerites that are proximal to the harpe.

label: basal transverse carina of third abdominal tergite
Defs: The carina that extends along the proximal margin of the third abdominal tergite.

label: third abdominal tergite
Defs: The tergite that is located in the third abdominal segment.

label: basal vein
Defs: The wing vein that is basally located on the fore wing and connects or nearly connects the submarginal vein and the medial plus cubital veins.

label: basalare
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the dorsal margin of the pectus of pterothoracic segment anteriorly of the pleural wing articulation.

label: pterothorax
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the meso- and metathorax and if the latter is fused with, the first abdominal tergum.

label: basiconic capitate peg sensillum
Defs: na

label: basicosta
Defs: The ridge that is located proximally and submarginally in the coxa.

label: coxa
Defs: The leg segment that is connected to the body and to the trochanter via conjunctivae and muscles.

label: basicostal suture
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the basicosta.

label: basicoxite
Defs: The area that is located on the coxa proximal to the basicostal suture.

label: eusternum
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the thoracic sternum posteriorly of the spinasternum.

label: basitarsal notch
Defs: The notch that is located proximally on the median surface of the probasitarsus.

label: probasitarsus
Defs: The basitarsus that is located on the protarsus.

label: basitarsus
Defs: The tarsomere that is the proximal most annulus of the tarsus, connected proximally with the tibia and distally with the second tarsomere via membranous conjunctivae.

label: tarsomere
Defs: The annulus that is the part of the tarsus.

label: tarsus
Defs: The leg segment that is apical to the tibia.

label: basiura
Defs: The area that is the proximal part of the gonossiculus and corresponds to the site of insertion of median parossiculo-gonossiculal muscle.

label: basivalvula
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of small sclerites and is located proximally on the first valvulae.

label: first valvula
Defs: The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is delimited distally by the proximal margin of the aulax.

label: blade
Defs: The area that is located distally on the mandible.

label: segment
Defs: An anatomical structure that is metameric and is connected to other metameric subdivisions by muscles and is delimited by its sclerites.

label: bulla
Defs: The anatomical region of the wing vein that is less melanized and more flexible than surrounding anatomical wing vein regions and corresponds to the intersection of the wing vein with a flexion line.

label: calcar
Defs: na

label: calyx
Defs: The anatomical space that is located anteriorly in the lateral oviduct and which receives the ovariole pedicels.

label: female genitalia
Defs: The genitalia that is part of the female organism.

label: cardo
Defs: The sclerite that is articulated with the cranium at the cranio-cardinal articulation, is connected to the stipes distolaterally via the stipitocardinal hinge and receives the site of attachment of the cranio-cardinal muscle.

label: maxilla
Defs: The appendage that is encircled by the area that is proximally delimited by the hypostoma posteriorly, the median margin of the mandible laterally, the labrum anterolaterally and the labium medially.

label: cenchrus
Defs: The conjunctiva that is folded and located on the anterior margin of the metanotum and covered (at least partially) with setae.

label: conjunctiva
Defs: The area of the cuticle that is weakly sclerotized, with thin exocuticle.

label: metanotum
Defs: The alinotum that is located in the metathorax, is connected with the mesoscutellum and the mesopostnotum anteriorly and the acrotergite of the first abdominal tergum posteromedially.

label: cercus
Defs: The sense organ that located apicolaterally on one of the apicalmost abdominal terga and attaches to a large nerve cord.

label: cervical apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located posteriorly of and continuous with the cervical prominence and corresponds to the site of insertion of laterocervical muscles.

label: cervical prominence
Defs: The articular process that is located on the anterior margin of the propleuron and bears the cranial condyle of the propleuron.

label: propleuron
Defs: The pleuron that is articulated with the fore leg, connected dorsolaterally (anterolaterally) with the pronotum and ventrally (posteriorly) with the prosternum.

label: cervical pronotal area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the pronotum and is delimited laterally by the epomial carina.

label: pronotal neck
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is delimited posterodorsally by an edge and that accommodates the posterior surface of the head.

label: cervical sclerite
Defs: na

label: cervix
Defs: na

label: chaetobothria
Defs: The row of stout spines that is located along the anterior edge of the protibia.

label: tibia
Defs: The leg segment that is proximal to the tarsus and distal to the femur.

label: chalaza
Defs: The seta that is located on a process.

label: chamber of the metanotum
Defs: The anatomical space that is delimited dorsally by the wall of the metascutellum, anteriorly and posteriorly by the bifurcated internal metanotal ridge.

label: cheek
Defs: The area that is located ventrally in between the eye and the oral foramen.

label: cibarium
Defs: The anatomical space that is the anteriormost part of the alimentary canal and is delimited proximally by the proximomedian margin of the sitophore and distally by the functional mouth.

label: circumocular ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the margin of the compound eye and corresponds to the ocular suture.

label: claval fold
Defs: The wing fold that is located on the fore wing, parallels the anal vein, and extends to the claval notch on the wing margin.

label: wing crease
Defs: The line along which the wing is creased.

label: claval lobe
Defs: The wing region that is posterior to the claval furrow and anterior to the jugal fold.

label: wing region
Defs: The area that is delimited by flexion and fold lines on the wing.

label: cleaning brush
Defs: The setiferous patch that is used to clean anatomical structures.

label: setiferous patch
Defs: The patch that differs from the surrounding region by having denser setae.

label: leg
Defs: The appendage that is composed of the coxa and all distal leg segments and is connected to the pectus.

label: closed coxal cavity
Defs: na

label: club
Defs: na

label: ventral rim of clypeus
Defs: The rim that extends along the distal margin of the clypeus.

label: clypeal process
Defs: The process that is located medially on the clypeus.

label: clypeo-pleurostomal line
Defs: The line that extends from the anterior tentorial pit to the cranial margin and separates the clypeus laterally from the pleurostoma.

label: coeloconic sensillum
Defs: na

label: colleterial gland
Defs: The glandula mucosa that secretes an adhesive substance used to fasten the eggs to a support.

label: protibial comb
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the apical margin of the fore tibia inbetween the articulations of the basitarsus and the calcar.

label: fore tibia
Defs: The tibia that is located on the fore leg.

label: comb of the spur
Defs: The row that is located on the calcar and is composed of hairlike spines.

label: compound eye
Defs: The compound organ that is composed of ommatidia.

label: condylar carina of the mandible
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends posteriorly on the lateral surface of the mandible from the mandibular condyle.

label: condylar groove
Defs: The impression that extends ventrally of the condylar carina of the mandible.

label: condyle
Defs: The articular surface that is convex and is inserted into the fossa of an adjacent sclerite.

label: articular surface
Defs: The area that is located on the sclerite and that makes movable direct contact with another sclerite.

label: corbicula
Defs: The area that is located on the metatibia and is delimited by a fringe of setae arising from the metatibial margins.

label: metatibia
Defs: The tibia that is located on the hind leg.

label: coronal suture
Defs: The suture that is located medially and is part of the epicranial suture.

label: groove
Defs: The line that is located on the sclerite and is impressed.

label: epicranial suture
Defs: The suture that is Y-shaped and located dorsally on the cranium.

label: costa
Defs: The wing vein that is anterior to the subcosta and is connected to the humeral plate.

label: costal cell
Defs: The membranous region of the forewing anterior to the submarginal vein, measured from the basal constriction that delimits the apex of the humeral plate of the wing to the point at which the submarginal vein touches the leading edge of the wing.

label: costal notch
Defs: The wing membrane that is located between the costal vein and the pterostigma.

label: wing membrane
Defs: The area that is not vein and not sclerotised.

label: leg segment
Defs: The segment that is part of a leg.

label: coxal foramen
Defs: The foramen that is located lateroventrally of the pectus, in which the coxa is positioned.

label: foramen
Defs: The anatomical space that is surrounded by sclerites and allows for the passage of haemolymph, nerves and tracheae.

label: coxal corium
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the coxa to the pectus.

label: cranial condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located on the cranium.

label: cranio-antennal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the cranium and inserts on the scape.

label: antennal muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts on the antenna.

label: cranio-pharyngeal plate muscle
Defs: The head muscle that arises internally from the face and inserts on the pharyngeal plate.

label: head muscle
Defs: The muscle that is located in the head.

label: head capsule
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the cranium and compound eye cuticle.

label: crest
Defs: na

label: crossvein
Defs: na

label: cubital vein
Defs: The longitudinal vein that is posterior to the marginal vein.

label: cupula
Defs: The sclerite that is connected via conjunctiva and attached via muscles to abdominal tergum 9 and the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: phallobase
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the cupulae, gonostipites and volsellae.

label: cuspis
Defs: The projection that is located apicolaterally on the parossiculus and is adjacent to the digitus.

label: dicondylic joint
Defs: The joint that is composed of two sclerites connected with to articulations.

label: joint
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of two sclerites connected by at least one articulation and the articular membrane located connecting the two sclerite.

label: dilator muscle apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the dilator muscle of the propodeal spiracle.

label: metapectal-propodeal complex
Defs: The sclerite that is connected anteriorly with the mesopectus dorsally with the metanotum, the metabasalare, second axillary sclerite of the hind wing and the metasubalare and articulates with the metacoxae and the metasoma.

label: discrimen
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds with the discrimenal lamella.

label: pectus
Defs: The sclerite that is located ventrally of the thoracic segment and bears the furca and the lateral coxal condyle of the pleuron.

label: discrimenal lamella
Defs: The ridge that is median, longitudinal and arises anteriorly from the base of the furca.

label: apical gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsellal complex-harpal muscle that arises from the distolateral margin of the gonostyle/volsellal complex and inserts on the lateral wall of the harpe.

label: male genitalia muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the male genitalia.

label: gonostipes
