Defs: The sclerite that is located dorsolaterally on the gonostyle/volsella complex, is connected to the distal margin of the cupula, to the proximal margin of the harpe, and to the lateral margin of the volsella.

label: harpe
Defs: The sclerite that is located distally on the gonostyle/volsella complex and does not connected to the cupula and to the volsella by conjunctiva or muscles.

label: distal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/parossiculal muscle that arises distally of the lateral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the distal part of the parossiculus distally of the site of origin of the proximal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle.

label: gonostyle-parossiculal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle, is proximomedially oriented, and inserts on the proximalmost sclerite of the volsella.

label: distal tarsal plantula
Defs: The tarsal plantula that arises distally on the tarsomere.

label: tarsal plantula
Defs: The projection that is median, membraneous and is located distally on the ventral margin of the tarsomere.

label: distivolsellar apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located distally on the parossiculus and is the site of insertion of the gonostyle/volsella complex-gonostyle muscle.

label: distodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The dorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises distodorsally from the gonostyle volsella complex and inserts on the proximal region of the penisvalva.

label: penisvalva
Defs: The sclerite that is in the middle of the external male genitalia, surrounds the distal part of the ductus ejaculatorius and the endophallus.

label: distoventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises from the proximoventral part of the gonostyle/volsella complex, inserts medially on the penisvalva and is oriented distodorsally.

label: ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The penisvalval muscle that arises ventrally from the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: dorsal axillar area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the axilla and is delimited laterally by the axillar carina and posteromedially by scutoscutellar sulcus.

label: dorsal cibarial dilatator muscle
Defs: na

label: dorsal incision of the pronotum
Defs: The notch that is located submedially on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and fits with the anterior extension of the preaxilla.

label: dorsal mesofurco-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that originates from the lateral part of the lateral mesofurcal arm and inserts on the posterior surface of the posterior profurcal lamella.

label: dorsal mesometapleural carina
Defs: The carina that extends along the dorsal margin of the mesometapleuron.

label: mesometapleuron
Defs: The sclerite that is comprised of the fused meso- and metapleura.

label: dorsal mesopleural inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron anterior to the subalar pit and articulates with the second axillary sclerite.

label: dorsal mesopostnotal flange
Defs: The area that is more heavily sclerotised than surrounding areas, traverse the mesopostnotum, unites laterally with the dorsal mesopostnotal flange, continuous laterally with the laterophragma and dorsally (anteriorly) with the pseudophragma and is located anterior to the ventral mesopostnotal flange.

label: mesopostnotum
Defs: The sclerite that bears the mesophragma and the mesolaterophragma.

label: dorsal mesopostnotal incision
Defs: The notch that is situated medially on the dorsal margin of the mesopostnotum.

label: dorsal metafurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends along the lateral metafurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the metafurco-second abdominal sternal muscle.

label: metafurcal arm
Defs: The apodeme that arises ventromedially form the metapectus, extends towards the metapleural apodeme and corresponds to the site of origin of metacoxal and metatrochanteral muscles.

label: dorsal metapleural area
Defs: The area that is delimited posterodorsally by the metapleural carina and anteroventrally by the metapleural sulcus.

label: metapleuron
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located laterally of the metadiscrimen.

label: dorsal pharyngeal dilatator
Defs: The pharyngeal muscle that arises on the inner proximal surface of the upper face, laterally to the origin of the anterior fronto-labral muscle, but mesally to the posterior fronto-labral muscle.

label: pharyngeal muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the pharynx.

label: pharyngeal wall
Defs: The area that is anterior on the foregut and that is situated posterior to the cibarium.

label: dorsal plate
Defs: na

label: dorsal premental adductor
Defs: The tentorio-labial muscle that arises from the cranium and inserts distally on the labium adjacent to the level of the salivary orifice.

label: tentorio-labial muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises from the cranium and inserts on the labium.

label: prementum
Defs: The sclerite that is median, is connected via conjunctiva along its proximolateral margins to the stipites, is articulated with the labial palps, is continuous along its distal margin with the ligula and distolateral margins with the distal hypopharynx and receives the site of attachments of the extrinsic labial palp muscles.

label: tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that extends between the posterior tentorial pit and the anterior tentorial pit.

label: dorsal profurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends dorsally on the profurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsal and ventral profurco-postoccipital muscles.

label: dorsal profurco-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the dorsal part of the lateral area of the dorsal profurcal lamella and inserts on the postocciput.

label: profurco-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the profurca and inserts on the postocciput.

label: postocciput
Defs: The area that is delimited by the postoccipital sulcus or postoccipital carina and the occipital foramen and bears the propleural fossa of the cranium.

label: dorsal pronotal area
Defs: The area that is delimited ventrally by the pronotal suprahumeral sulcus and corresponds to the site of origin of the pronoto-procoxal, pronoto-postoccipital, pronoto-laterocervical and the pronoto-propleural muscles.

label: dorsal pronotal corner
Defs: The corner that is located submedially on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and that is adjacent to the anterolateral mesoscutal corner.

label: dorsal pronotal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and supports the anterior inflection of the mesoscutum.

label: dorsal propleural area
Defs: The area that is located posterodorsally of the well-sclerotized lateral propleural area and usually differs from it in sculpture.

label: dorsal propleural ridge
Defs: The ridge that is marginal or submarginal, extends along the dorsal margin of the propleuron and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral propleuro-postoccipital muscle.

label: dorsal propodeal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the propodeum and accommodates the metanotum.

label: dorsal rod
Defs: The sclerite that is located dorsally between the penisvalvae.

label: dorsal premento-salivarial muscle
Defs: The salivarial muscle that inserts proximodorsally on the salivary duct.

label: salivarial muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the dorsal wall of the salivarium or the salivarial sclerite.

label: dorsal salivarial wall
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends dorsally of the salivarial sclerite between the distal boundary of the salivary duct and the salivary orifice. The dorsal premento-salivarial muscle inserts on the dorsal salivarial wall.

label: dorsal tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that arises anterodorsally from the anterior tentorial arm and extends to the anterior wall of the cranium.

label: anterior tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that extends between the anterior tentorial pit and the tentorial bridge.

label: dorsal tooth of mandible
Defs: The apical tooth of mandible that is located closest to the clypeus.

label: apical tooth of mandible
Defs: The tooth that is located apically on the external margin of the mandible.

label: dorso-pleural line
Defs: The anatomical line that is located between the dorsum and the pleuron.

label: dorsolateral cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that arises from the dorsolateral part of the cupula, just laterally of the site of origin of the dorsomedian cupulo-gonostipal muscle, and inserts on the dorsolateral part of the gonostipes.

label: cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the cupula and inserts on the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: dorsomedial cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that inserts medially on the dorsal region of the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: male genitalia
Defs: The genitalia that is part of the male organism.

label: dorsope
Defs: The pit that is located at the proximal end of the dorsal carina on the abdominal tergum 2.

label: pit
Defs: The patch that is impressed and corresponds to an apophysis.

label: dorsum
Defs: The area of the segment that is dorsal.

label: duct
Defs: The cavitated compound organ that is canal-like, layered with epithelial cells and leads from an exocrine gland or organ.

label: ductus ejaculatorius
Defs: The duct(s) that is(are) connect vasa deferentia with endophallus and is(are) ectodermal in origin.

label: internal male genitalia
Defs: The compound organ that functions as producer and transporter of sperm, spermatophore and semen, composed of the testes, vas deferens, accessory glands and ductus ejaculatorius. Ecto- and mesodermal in origin.

label: ectophallus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites and muscles of the external male genitalia.

label: anellus
Defs: The flagellomere that is located proximally on the flagellum and lacks longitudinal sensilla.

label: empodium
Defs: na

label: encircling groove
Defs: The anatomical space that surrounds the plate-like structure in a multiporous plate sensillum.

label: endocuticle
Defs: The procuticle that is not tanned (sclerotised, proteins scarcely crosslinked) and located between the Schmidt\'s layer and the exocuticle.

label: procuticle
Defs: The cuticle that containes chitin fibrils and is located between the Schmidt\'s layer and the epicuticle.

label: endophallus
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the gonopore with the penisvalvae.

label: epicnemial pit
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is located at the lateral end of the epicnemial carina.

label: epicnemium
Defs: The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the procoxa.

label: scrobe
Defs: The area that is impressed and is for the reception or concealment of another sclerite.

label: mesopectus
Defs: The sclerite that is U-shaped in cross section, connected anteriorly with the pronotum and the propectus, dorsally with the basalare, the mesonotum, the second axillary sclerite and the subalare, posteriorly with the metapectus and bears the mesodiscrimenal lamella and the mesofurca.

label: epicoxal lobe
Defs: The area that is located posteroventrally on the propleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the epicoxal sulcus.

label: epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is dorsal to the coxal foramen.

label: epidermis
Defs: The epithelium that is located in the integument and composed of epidermal cells.

label: epimeron
Defs: The area that is located on the pleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the pleural sulcus.

label: epipharyngeal wall
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends between the distal margin of the labrum and the proximal boundary of the cibarium.

label: preoral cavity
Defs: The anatomical cluster that includes the labrum, hypopharynx and labium.

label: epipharynx
Defs: The lobe that is located distally on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: epipygium
Defs: The flange that is located on abdominal tergum 10, between the cerci.

label: flange
Defs: The projection that is lamella-like and is located on a rim, carina, apodeme or edge.

label: epistomal declivity
Defs: The notch that is located on the ventral margin of the clypeus.

label: epistomal ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds to the epistomal sulcus.

label: epistomal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the epistomal line.

label: epomial carina
Defs: The carina that is vertical, crosses the pronotum and separates the lateral pronotal area from the median pronotal area.

label: ergot
Defs: The apodeme that is lateral, located medially on the penisvalva and corresponds to the sites of insertion of the lateral and distoventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle and the parossiculo-penisvalval muscles.

label: thoracic sternum
Defs: The sternum that is located on a thoracic segment.

label: evaporatorium
Defs: The area that is highly sculptured and surrounds the opening of a gland.

label: exocuticle
Defs: The procuticle that is tanned (sclerotised, proteins are highly crosslinked) and located between the endocuticle and epicuticle.

label: external paramera
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the gonostipites and volsellae.

label: premento-palpal muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises from the prementum and inserts on the first sclerite of the labial palp.

label: labial muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the labium.

label: labial palp
Defs: The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the labial palp.

label: exuvia
Defs: The cuticle that is discarded after a molt.

label: facial fovea
Defs: The area that is concave, narrow, often finely and densely pubescent and extends along the inner orbit.

label: facial orbit
Defs: The line that extends along the border of the eye and lower face.

label: orbit
Defs: The margin of the compound eye.

label: facial pit
Defs: The pit that overlaps with the facial apodeme.

label: facial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that arises medially from the ventral margin of the median ocellus and extends towards the intertorular carina.

label: fascia
Defs: The band that is transverse and composed of setae in Apoidea.

label: felt field
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located sublaterally on an abdominal sternum.

label: felt line
Defs: The band that is composed of flattened setae and secretory pores and is located laterally on abdominal tergum 3.

label: genitalia
Defs: The anatomical system that is involved in copulation, fertilization and/or oviposition.

label: femoral depression
Defs: na

label: femoral groove
Defs: The scrobe that is located on the mesopleuron into which the mesofemur fits when pressed against the mesosoma.

label: femur
Defs: The leg segment that is distal to the trochanter and proximal to the tibia.

label: fibula ducti
Defs: The sclerite that is located in the proximal end of the unpaired part of the ductus ejaculatorius.

label: first abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is the anteriormost in the body.

label: abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that has attachment for both an occlusor and a dilator muscle.

label: first axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that articulates with the mesonotum.

label: first median plate
Defs: The sclerite that is located between the second axillary and the distal arm of the third axillary at the base of the mediocubital field.

label: median complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of median plates.

label: first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The mesonotal muscle that arises ventrally from the mesopectus and inserts on the mesoscutum laterally of the notauli and medially of the parascutal carina.

label: mesonotal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesonotum.

label: mesonotum
Defs: The area that is limited anteriorly by the pronotum, laterally by the basalare, axillary sclerites, subalare and the mesopectus and posterolaterally by the mesopostnotum and the metanotum.

label: first phragmo-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that originates from the first phragma and inserts on the postocciput.

label: postoccipital muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the postocciput.

label: prophragma
Defs: The phragma that extends along the anterior margin of the mesonotum.

label: first phragmo-propleural muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises medially from the prophragma and inserts on the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron.

label: propleural muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts on the propleuron.

label: first phragmo-second phragmal muscle
Defs: The mesophragmal muscle that extends between the prophragma and mesophragma.

label: mesophragmal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesophragma.

label: mesophragma
Defs: The phragma that extends along the ventral (posterior) margin of the ventral mesopostnotal flange and corresponds to the site of origin of the prophragmo-mesophragmal and the mesophragmo-metaphragmal muscles.

label: distal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle that inserts on the median wall of the harpe and arises distally of the site of origin of the proximal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts on the harpe.

label: first subdiscal
Defs: The wing cell that is located on the wing.

label: first valvifer
Defs: The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is proximal to the aulax, bears the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the second valviferal condyle of the first valvifer and is connected to the genital membrane by muscle.

label: first valvifer-first valvula complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that articulate with the ninth abdominal tergite and the second valvifer.

label: fissure
Defs: The line that secondarily divides a sclerite.

label: flabellum
Defs: The sclerite that is located at the apex of the glossa in Apoidea.

label: foramen genitale
Defs: The anatomical space that is surrounded by the proximal margin of the cupula.

label: occipital foramen
Defs: The foramen that is delimited dorsally by the postocciput.

label: fore coxa
Defs: na

label: wing
Defs: The appendage that is between the notum and the pectus and is connected to the body by the axillary sclerite muscles.

label: mesothorax
Defs: The thoracic segment that is located between the prothorax and the metathorax and is delimited by the mesopectus and the mesonotum.

label: forewing
Defs: na

label: frenal line
Defs: The line that is transverse, arched anteriorly and is continuous with the posterior margins of the mesoscutellar arms.

label: frenum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the mesoscutellum and is delimited anteriorly by the frenal line.

label: frontal line
Defs: The line that is median and extending on the frons.

label: frontal orbit
Defs: The area that extends along the lateral margin of the upper face.

label: frontal patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the frons.

label: frontal scrobe
Defs: na

label: frontal suture
Defs: The suture that diverges ventrally (or anteriorly) from the coronal suture between the antennal foramina toward the anterior articulations of the mandibles.

label: functional mouth
Defs: The anatomical space that is delimited posteriorly by the distal part of the sitophore and anteriorly by the tormae.

label: funicle
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of flagellomeres located between the pedicel and clava or the distalmost anellus and clava.

label: funicle segment
Defs: The annulus that is located in the funicle.

label: furca
Defs: The apodeme that arises medially from the ventral part of the thorax and corresponds to the site of origin of interfurcal and coxal muscles.

label: furcal arm
Defs: The furca that is paired, arises medioventrally from the sternum and corresponds to the furcal pit.

label: furcal pit
Defs: The pit that corresponds to the furca.

label: furcasternum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the prosternum and bears the profurca.

label: galea
Defs: The lobe that is located on the stipes at the distal part of the posterior stipital sclerite distolateral to the lacinia.

label: gaster
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of all abdominal segments posterior to abdominal segment 2.

label: gastrocoelus
Defs: The area that is concave, transverse, and located anterolaterally on abdominal tergum 3.

label: genal bridge
Defs: na

label: genal patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the gena.

label: labium
Defs: The appendage that is encircled by the area that is proximally delimited by the lateral margins of the cardo and the posterior stipital sclerite laterally, and the anatomical line that is tangential to the salivary duct and traverses the salivary orifice anteriorly.

label: premento-glossal muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises on the ventral part of the prementum, laterally to the ventral premento-salivarial muscle and inserts on the anterior glossal plate.

label: glymma
Defs: The groove that is located between the spiracle and the anterior margin of abdominal tergum 2.

label: gonad
Defs: The compound organ that makes gametes.

label: reproductive system
Defs: The anatomical system that is involved in reproduction.

label: gonocondyle
Defs: The apophysis that is located ventromedially on the proximal margin of the cupula and is the site of insertion of the lateral S9-cupulal muscle.

label: gonoforceps
Defs: The sclerite that is located distally of the cupula and dorsolaterally of the volsella, surrounds the aedeagus dorsolaterally and does not connected to any sclerite distally.

label: gonomacula
Defs: The conjunctiva that is located at the distal apex of the harpe.

label: gonopod
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the gonostipites, volsellae and harpes.

label: gonossiculo-phallotremal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the basiura and inserts on the endophallus.

label: volsella
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites on the ventral part of the male genitalia that are not connected to the cupula via muscles.

label: gonostipo-volsellal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises proximally from the ventral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the volsella at the border between the gono- and parossiculi.

label: gonostyle
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of sclerites located distally of the cupula dorsolaterally of the volsella, and that surround the aedeagus.

label: gradulus
Defs: The carina that is transverse and posteriorly directed laterally and is located on the abdominal tergite.

label: gula
Defs: na

label: gular ridge
Defs: na

label: gular sulcus
Defs: na

label: hamulus
Defs: The seta that is located on the anterior margin of the hind wing and interlocks with the recurved posterior edge of the fore wing in Hymenoptera during flight, making them functionally one winged.

label: hind wing
Defs: The wing that is located on the metathorax.

label: harpo-gonomaculal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises form the harpe and inserts on the gonomacula.

label: hind leg
Defs: The leg that is located on the metathorax.

label: metathorax
Defs: The thoracic segment that is located between the mesothorax and the first abdominal tergum and is delimited by the metanotum and the metapectus.

label: hindwing
Defs: na

label: humeral plate
Defs: The sclerite that articulates with the proximal end of the costal vein.

label: humeral sclerite of the metanotum
Defs: The sclerite that is connected to the lateral margin of the metanotum and bears the anterior metanotal wing process.

label: hymenopteran
Defs: The multi-cellular organism that is classified in Hymenoptera.

label: hyperoccipital carina
Defs: The carina that extends on the vertex between the outer orbits.

label: hypoclypeal depression
Defs: The anatomical space that is delimited anteriorly by the clypeus and posteriorly by the labrum.

label: oral foramen
Defs: The foramen that is located anteriorly/ventrally on the cranium in which the mouthparts are positioned.

label: hypopharyngeal rod
Defs: The ligament that connects the proximolateral margin of the prementum with the proximal part of the ligula.

label: ligament
Defs: The area that is resilin rich.

label: hypopharynx
Defs: The area that is delimited proximally by the proximal margin of the sitophore, distally by the salivarial orifice.

label: mouthparts
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the labrum, epipharyngeal wall, hypopharyngeal wall (including the sitophore), mandibles, maxillae, labium and conjunctivae connecting them.

label: hypopygium
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is the posteriormost visible sclerite located ventrally in the abdomen.

label: hypostoma
Defs: The area that extends on the posterior (ventral) margin of the oral foramen along the site of attachments of the conjunctiva connecting the cranium with the maxillae and is delimited laterally by the pleurostomal fossa.

label: hypostomal bridge
Defs: The subforaminal bridge that is delimited laterally by the dorsally extended hypostomal carina.

label: subforaminal bridge
Defs: The area that is located between the oral and the occipital foramina.

label: hypostomal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the hypostoma from the cranium.

label: hypostomal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the posteroventral margin of the cranium between the pleurostomal fossae and delimits the hypostoma.

label: hypostomal suture
Defs: na

label: hypostomal tooth
Defs: The projection that is located on the posterolateral margin of the oral foramen at the junction of the hypostoma and the pleurostomal fossa.

label: mouth margin
Defs: The edge that is located on the cranium along the oral foramen.

label: inner orbit
Defs: The line that extends along the border between the eye and face.

label: integrated tarsal plantula
Defs: The tarsal plantula that arises medially on the tarsomere.

label: interantennal process
Defs: The area that is elevated and extends between the antennal rims.

label: interantennal process
Defs: na

label: interantennal prominence
Defs: na

label: interaxillar sulcus
Defs: The median sulcus of the mesonotum between the anterior margin of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex and the anterior margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: intercoxal space
Defs: The area that is located between the acetabular carina and the ventral mesopleural carina.

label: internal metanotal ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds to the metascutellar arm.

label: interocellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located on the upper face between lateral ocelli and corresponds internally with a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

label: interocellar space
Defs: The area that is limited posteriorly by the posterior ocellar line and laterally by the lateral ocellar line.

label: interommatidial seta
Defs: The seta that is located at the intersection of the margins of three ommatidiae.

label: interorbital space
Defs: The interocular distance that is the shortest between the inner margin of compound eyes.

label: interocular distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the anteroposterior body axis and extends between the medial margins of the compound eyes.

label: interpenisvalval muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that connects the valvurae.

label: intersegmental membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects two segments.

label: intersegmental membrane-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the intersegmental membrane between the pronotum and the mesopectus and inserts on the mesobasalare.

label: mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesobasalare.

label: mesobasalare
Defs: The basalare that is located in the mesothorax.

label: mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane
Defs: The intersegmental membrane that is located between the mesopectus and the pronotum.

label: intersegmentalia
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the intersegmental membrane.

label: intersternite
Defs: The intersegmentalia that is located in between sterna.

label: mesosoma
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: interstice
Defs: The area that is unsculptured and is delimited by striae or punctures.

label: intertorular carina
Defs: The carina that extends between the dorsal margin of the antennal rims.

label: intervalvula
Defs: The sternal sclerite in the venter of the ninth abdominal segment between the second valvifers.

label: intervolsellal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that connects the proximal part of parossiculi.

label: intrinsic muscle of the 9th sternum
Defs: The sternal muscle that connects the lateral margins of the abdominal tergum 9 and extends internally of the external male genitalia.

label: sternal muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the abdominal sternum.

label: intrinsic muscle of the gonostipes
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that connects the dorsal and ventral part of the gonostipes.

label: intrinsic palpal muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises from a palpal sclerite and inserts on the palpal sclerite distal to it.

label: jugal region
Defs: The wing region that is delimited by the plica jugalis.

label: juxtantennal carina
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and mesal to the antennal base.

label: supraclypeal area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the lower face between the dorsal margin of the clypeus and the anatomical line that connects the dorsalmost points of the left and right antennal rims.

label: kleisiades
Defs: The area that is located apically on the gonostyle when it consist only from one sclerite and set off partly by conjunctiva. The kleisiades is never connected to the proximal part of the gonostyle via muscles.

label: labial endite
Defs: na

label: labial gland
Defs: The gland that empties between the base of the hypopharynx and the labium, or on the hypopharynx.

label: palpus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the palpal segments.

label: labial suture
Defs: na

label: labiomaxillary complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the labium and maxillae.

label: labral compressor
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that arises from the proximal part of the labrum and inserts on the distal epipharyngeal wall.

label: epipharyngeal muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: labral seta
Defs: The seta that is located on the labrum.

label: lacinial lobe
Defs: The lobe that extends proximally on the distal margin of the medial stipital wall, is adjacent to the basal lacinial sclerite, overlaps the proximal part of the galea.

label: lamella
Defs: na

label: larval abdomen
Defs: The larval tagma that is located posterior to the thorax.

label: larval tagma
Defs: The tagma that is located in the larva.

label: larval head
Defs: The larval tagma that is located anterior to the thorax.

label: larval thorax
Defs: The larval tagma that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and metathorax and is located between the head and the abdomen.

label: lateral S9-cupulal muscle
Defs: The S9-cupulal muscle that arises sublaterally from S9 and inserts medioventrally on the cupula.

label: abdominal tergite 9
Defs: The tergite that is located on the abdominal segment 9

label: lateral apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located laterally on the proximal margin of abdominal tergum 9.

label: lateral area of the mesoscutum
Defs: The area that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina.

label: lateral articular process
Defs: The projection that is located on the prolpeuron posterolaterally of the epicoxal lobe and bears the procoxal condyle of the propleuron.

label: lateral axillar area
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the axilla and is delimited medially by the axillar carina.

label: lateral bar of the mesoscutellum
Defs: The bar that extends from the dorsal axillar area to the mesoscutellum.

label: lateral basisternal projection
Defs: The area that is located anterolaterally on the basisternum and forms the median propleural site of articulation with the procoxa.

label: lateral carina of abdominal tergite 3
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of abdominal tergite 3.

label: lateral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises anterolaterally of the site of origin of the distodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle and inserts laterally on the penisvalva.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts on the penisvalva.

label: median gonostyle/volsella complex-volsella muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-volsellal muscle that arises medially of the submedian conjunctiva on the distoventral margin of gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-volsellal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises proximoventrally from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts nearby the gonossiculal articulation.

label: lateral margin of mesoscutum
Defs: The inflection that extends along the anterolateral margin of the mesoscutum and fit with the dorsal pronotal inflection.

label: lateral mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises laterally from the lateral mesofurcal arm, laterally to the site of origin  of the median mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the mesotrochanter.

label: mesotrochanter
Defs: The trochanter that is located on the mid leg.

label: lateral mesoscutellar spine
Defs: The projection that is located on the posterodorsal margin of the axillula.

label: lateral metapleuro-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that originates ventrally of the metapleural ridge and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.

label: metacoxal muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the metacoxa.

label: metacoxa
Defs: The coxa that is located on the hind leg.

label: lateral neck plate
Defs: na

label: lateral ocellar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the margins of the  median and lateral ocelli.

label: lateral ocellus
Defs: The ocellus that is paired.

label: ocellus
Defs: The multi-tissue structure that is located on the top of the head, composed of the corneal lens, pigment cell, rhabdoms and synaptic plexus.

label: lateral profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: na

label: lateral pronotal area
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is lateral and delimited medially by the epomial carina.

label: lateral propleural area
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the propleuron and is delimited by the longitudinal carina of the propleuron.

label: lateral propodeal area
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the propodeum, is delimited posteromedially by the lateral propodeal carina and is delimited laterally by the plica.

label: propodeum
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located posterior to the metapleural sulcus.

label: lateral propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that is oblique and arises submedially from the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex and extends to the posterior propodeal projection.

label: propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the propodeum.

label: lateral scutellar keel
Defs: The carina which is present on the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: scutellar disc
Defs: The area that is median, convex and is delimited anteriorly by the scutoscutellar sulcus and laterally by the axillar depression.

label: lateral scutellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located along the posterolateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: lateral suspensor of the mouth
Defs: The hypopharyngeal muscle that arises from the distal end of the anterior tentorial arm or from the inner surface of the head capsule and inserts on the lateral surface of the proximolateral processes of the sitophore.

label: hypopharyngeal muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the hypopharyngeal wall.

label: sitophore
Defs: The sclerite that is located in the proximal part of the hypopharygeal wall delimited distally by the functional mouth and proximally by the proximal boundary of the cibarium. The tentorio-hypopharyngeal muscle inserts on the proximal margin of the sitophore.

label: laterocervico-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the cervical apodeme and inserts on the procoxa on the opposite side from which it arises.

label: procoxal muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the procoxa.

label: laterope
Defs: The depression that is located laterally and proximally on abdominal tergum 2.

label: laterophragma
Defs: The apodeme that is located laterally on the postnotum.

label: postnotum
Defs: The sclerite that bears the phragma and is located posterior to a notum.

label: laterotergite
Defs: The tergite that is located laterally on the abdominal tergum.

label: ligula
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the glossa and paraglossae.

label: longitudinal carina of the propleuron
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the ventral propleural area.

label: longitudinal line of the dorsal profurcal lamella
Defs: The line that crosses the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior profurcal lamella.

label: longitudinal metacoxal carina
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and is located on the metacoxa.

label: longitudinal muscle of the sucking pump
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that is unpaired and arises from the distal part of the pharyngeal wall and inserts along most of the length of the proximal epipharyngeal wall.

label: longitudinal vein
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of abscissae extending along the long axis of the wing.

label: wing venation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of abscissae.

label: malar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the lower orbit and the ventrolateral margin of the cranium.

label: malar sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the ventral margin of the compound eye and the base of the mandible.

label: mandibular adductor muscle apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertion of the mandibular adductor muscle.

label: mandibular condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located ventrally (posteriorly) on the proximolateral edge of the mandible and inserts into the pleurostomal fossa.

label: mandibular gland
Defs: The gland that opens mesally at the base of the mandible.

label: marginal cilia
Defs: The row of setae that is located along the margin of the wing blade in the same plane as the wing blade.

label: marginal vein
Defs: The abscissa that is located along the anterior margin of the fore wing and is thought to correspond to the anterior abscissa of the radius (R1).

label: maxillary gland
Defs: The gland that opens medially at the bases of the maxillae.

label: maxillary palp
Defs: The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label: medial 9th sterno-cupulal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the spiculum and inserts on the gonocondyle.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus muscle
Defs: The gonossiculal muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts laterally on the gonossiculus.

label: gonossiculal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that inserts on the gonossiculus.

label: medial propodeal furrow
Defs: The impression that is longitudinal and located medially on the abdominal tergum 1.

label: propodeum
Defs: The area that is located dorsomedially on the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: medial vein
Defs: The wing vein that is posterior to the radial vein and is connected to the anterior margin of the anterior median plate.

label: median area of the mesoscutum
Defs: The area that is located between the notauli.

label: median mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the ventral surface of the lateral mesofurcal arm medial to the site of origin of the lateral mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: median mesoscutal line
Defs: The line that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the mesoscutum.

label: median mesoscutal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is a median mesoscutal line and that is adjacent to the (internal) median mesoscutal ridge.

label: median metapleuro-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the paracoxal ridge and from the metadiscrimenal lamella and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.

label: median oblique line
Defs: The depression that is oblique and located submedially on the mesopleuron between the fore coxa and posterolateral corner of the mesopleuron.

label: median ocellus
Defs: The ocellus that is located medially on the cranium.

label: median plate
Defs: na

label: median profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises partly from the posteroventral surface of the ventral profurcal lamella and partly from the ventral surface of the profurcal arm.

label: procoxa
Defs: The coxa that is located on the fore leg.

label: median propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that is oriented anteroposteriorly and is located medially on the propodeum.

label: median propodeal keel
Defs: na

label: median sclerotized style
Defs: The sclerite that is located ventrally between the penisvalvae.

label: median sulcus of postgenal bridge
Defs: The sulcus that is located on the postgenal suture.

label: postgenal bridge
Defs: The subforaminal bridge that is sclerotised and limited anteriorly (ventrally) by the hypostomal carina and is subdivided medially by the median sulcus of the postgenal bridge.

label: mediolateral S9-cupulal muscle
Defs: The cupulal muscle that arises medially from abdominal sternum 9 and inserts ventrolaterally on the cupula.

label: mentum
Defs: na

label: meron
Defs: The area that is located posterolaterally and proximally on the coxa, proximal to the basicostal suture.

label: mesepimeral inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the mesopectus.

label: mesepimeron
Defs: The epimeron that is located on the mesopleuron.

label: mesepimeral ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopectus.

label: mesepimeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopectus, delimits the mesepimeral area and corresponds to the mesepimeral ridge.

label: mesepisternal groove
Defs: A groove on the mesopleuron, extending ventrally from a pit under the base of the forewings and, when complete, reaching the anteroventral margin of the metathorax.

label: mesepisternum
Defs: The episternum that is located on the mesopleuron.

label: mesocoxal depression
Defs: The acetabulum that is located posteroventrally on the mesopectus, accommodates the mesocoxa and is delimited anterolaterally by the postpectal carina.

label: mesocoxo-mesosubalar muscle
Defs: The mesosubalare muscle that arises from the mesocoxa and inserts on the mesosubalare.

label: mesosubalare muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesosubalare.

label: mesosubalare
Defs: The subalare that is located in the mesothorax.

label: mid coxa
Defs: The coxa that is located on the mid leg.

label: mesodiscrimen
Defs: The discrimen that is located in the mesothorax and corresponds with the mesodiscrimenal lamella.

label: mesodiscrimenal lamella
Defs: The discrimenal lamella that is located in the mesothorax.

label: mesofurcal pit
Defs: The furcal pit that is located in the mesothorax.

label: mesofurco-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: mesolaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesolaterophragma.

label: mesofurco-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the metabasalare.

label: metabasalar muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metabasalare.

label: metabasalare
Defs: The basalare that is located in the metathorax.

label: mesometapleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that crosses the mesometapleuron from the posterolateral margin of the mesocoxal foramen to the mesopleural pit.

label: mesometapleural suture
Defs: The line of separation that is located between the mesopectus and the metapectus.

label: phragma
Defs: The antecosta that corresponds to the site of attachment of the dorsal longitudinal muscles in the thorax.

label: mesopleural carina
Defs: The carina that crosses the mesopleuron and limits ventrally the femoral depression.

label: mesopleural epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The epicoxal sulcus that is located on the mesopleuron.

label: mesopleural pit
Defs: na

label: mesopleural triangle
Defs: The area that is limited dorsally by the subalar ridge, posteroventrally by the speculum and ends posteriorly in the subalar pit.

label: mesopleuro-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that originates anteroventrally from the mesopleuron and insert on the mesobasalare.

label: mesopleuro-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The hind wing third axillary muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of hind wing.

label: hind wing third axillary muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the hind wing.

label: third axillary sclerite of the hind wing
Defs: The third axillary sclerite that is located on the metathorax.

label: mesopostscutellum
Defs: The area that is located posteromedially on the  mesoscutellum, is delimited anteriorly by the posterior scutellar depression.

label: mesoscutal humeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends medially along the parascutal carina and corresponds to a shallow ridge.

label: mesoscutal suprahumeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the mesoscutum between the anterior-most point of the preaxilla and the anteroadmedian line and corresponds to the vertical lobe of the mesoscutum.

label: mesoscutellar appendage
Defs: na

label: mesoscutello-metanotal muscle
Defs: The metanotal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the metanotum.

label: metanotal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metanotum.

label: scutellum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly of the scutoscutellar suture.

label: scutum
Defs: The area that is located on the alinotum and is situated anterior to the scutoscutellar suture.

label: mesospinasterno-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises from the mesospinasternum and inserts on the metafurca.

label: metafurcal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metafurca.

label: metafurca
Defs: The furca that is located medioventrally on the metapectus.

label: mesospinasternum
Defs: The spinasternum that is located between the mesopectus and metapectus.

label: mesosterno-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that originates at least partly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: mesosterno-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises anteriorly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts posteriorly on the procoxa.

label: mesosternum
Defs: The eusternum that is located in the mesothorax.

label: subalare
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the dorsal margin of the pterothoracic pectus posterior to the pleural wing articulation.

label: anterior thoracic spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that is located on the border of the pronotum and mesopleuron.

label: spiracle
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the distal end of the trachea and the margin of the sclerite or conjunctiva surrounding the spiracular opening.

label: mesotrochantin
Defs: The trochantin that is located in the mesothorax.

label: trochantin
Defs: The sclerite that is located anterolaterally of the coxa and corresponds to the site of insertion of the notal-trochantinal muscle.

label: mesotrochantinal plate
Defs: na

label: metacoxal depression
Defs: The acetabulum that is concave, is located ventrally on metapectal-propodeal complex and is delimited anteriorly by the transverse metepisternal carina and accommodates the base of the metacoxa.

label: metapectus
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the metapleural sulcus and ridge.

label: metacoxo-metasubalar muscle
Defs: The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metacoxa and inserts on the metasubalare.

label: metasubalare muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metasubalare.

label: metasubalare
Defs: The subalare that is located in the metathorax.

label: metadiscrimen
Defs: The discrimen that is located in the metathorax and corresponds to the metadiscrimenal lamella.

label: metadiscrimenal lamella
Defs: The discrimenal lamella that is located in the metathorax.

label: metafurcal pit
Defs: The furcal pit that is located in the metathorax.

label: metafurco-mesofurcal
Defs: na

label: metafurco-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that originates from the metafurca and inserts on the posterior margin of the metacoxa.

label: metafurco-metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The metatrochanteral muscle that arises from the metafurca and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.

label: metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the metatrochanter.

label: metatrochanter
Defs: The trochanter that is located on the hind leg.

label: metafurco-second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metafurca and inserts on abdominal sternum 2.

label: second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the second abdominal sternum.

label: metanotal spine
Defs: The median process on the metascutellum.

label: metascutellum
Defs: The area that is located posteromedially on the metanotum, is delimited laterally by the metanotal trough and corresponds to the reservoir of the dorsal vessel.

label: metanotal trough
Defs: The area that is concave, and is delimited medially by the metascutellum, laterally by the supraalar area and posteriorly by the metascutellar arm.

label: metanotal-propodeal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the fused metanotum and abdominal tergum 1 and delimit an anterior narrow, usually differently sculptured area.

label: metanoto-metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The metatrochanteral muscle that originates from the humeral sclerite and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.

label: metaphragma
Defs: The phragma that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesophragmo-metaphragmal and metaphragmo-second abdominal tergal muscles.

label: metapleural apodeme
Defs: The pleural apodeme that is connected with the metafurca.

label: pleural apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located on the pleuron.

label: metapleural arm
Defs: The area that is located anterodorsally on the metapleuron.

label: metapleural carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the metapleuron dorsally from the propodeum, extends from just ventral of the metapleural arm to the metacoxal articulation and passes anteroventral to the propodeal spiracle.

label: metapleural epicoxal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the metapleural triangle.

label: metapleural epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The epicoxal sulcus that extends anteriorly along and close to the metapleural epicoxal carina.

label: metapleural pit
Defs: The pleural pit that is corresponds to the metapleural apodeme.

label: pleural pit
Defs: The pit that is located on the pleuron and corresponds to the pleural apophysis.

label: metapleural ridge
Defs: The pleural ridge that corresponds to the metapleural sulcus.

label: pleural ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends between the pleural wing process and the lateral coxal articulation and marks the border between the episternum and epimeron.

label: metapleural sulcus
Defs: The line that corresponds with the metapleural ridge.

label: pleural suture
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the pleural ridge and separates the episternum from the epimeron.

label: metapleural triangle
Defs: The area that is located anteroventrally on the metapectus, is delimited ventrally by the ventral carina of the metapleuron and is triangular.

label: metapleuro-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metabasalare.

label: metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The metanotal muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metanotum.

label: metapleuro-metasubalar muscle
Defs: The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metasubalare.

label: metapleuro-metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The metatrochanteral muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.

label: metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The hind wing third axillary muscle that originates from the metapleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the hind wing.

label: metapostnotum
Defs: na

label: metascutellar arm
Defs: The area that is elevated and extends along the posterior margin of the metanotum from the metascutellum to the supraalar area.

label: metascutellar carina
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the metascutellum.

label: metasomal depression
Defs: The acetabulum that is concave, surrounds the nucha and accommodates the base of the metasoma.

label: metasternum
Defs: The eusternum that is located in the metathorax.

label: metepimeron
Defs: The epimeron that is located on the metapleuron and is located posteriorly of the metapleural sulcus.

label: metepisternal depression
Defs: The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the mesocoxa.

label: metepisternum
Defs: The episternum that is located anteroventrally of the metapleural sulcus.

label: mid leg
Defs: The leg that is located on the mesothorax.

label: midpit
Defs: The depression that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutum.

label: monocondylic joint
Defs: The joint that is composed of two sclerites that are connected with one articulation.

label: multiporous plate sensillum
Defs: The sensillum that corresponds to a multiporous plate.

label: muscle
Defs: The portion of tissue that is composed of contractile fibers.

label: muscle bearing process of the metanotum
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertions of the lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscles.

label: musculus retractor unguis
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that originates within the tibia and femur and has a long tendon that inserts through the terminal tarsomere onto the unguitractor.

label: intrinsic leg muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts and originates in the leg.

label: unguitractor plate
Defs: The sclerite that corresponds to the site of insertion of the flexor of the pretarsus.

label: netrion
Defs: The area that is located posteroventrally on the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of first flexor of the fore wing muscle.

label: netrion apodeme
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the netrion.

label: netrion sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that  anteriorly delimits the netrion.

label: notaulus
Defs: The line that extends submedially along the mesoscutum and corresponds to the median border of the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: notopleural suture
Defs: The suture that is located between the mesonotum and mesopleuron.

label: nucha
Defs: The area that is raised and surrounds the propodeal foramen.

label: occipital arch
Defs: The area that is located on the cranium and is delimited anteriorly by the occipital suture and posteriorly by the postoccipital sutures.

label: occipital carina
Defs: The carina that surrounds dorsolaterally the occiput.

label: propleural fossa of the cranium
Defs: The fossa that articulates with the cranial condyle of the propleuron.

label: occipital depression
Defs: The depression that is located submedially on the occiput, ventral to the occipital carina.

label: occiput
Defs: The area that is concave and surrounds the postocciput.

label: occipital sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is paired, extends dorsally from the posterior tentorial pit towards lateral ocellus and corresponds with the occipital ridge.

label: occiptal condyle
Defs: na

label: occlusor muscle apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the occlusor muscle of the thoracic spiracle.

label: ocellar fovea
Defs: The depression that extends along the lateral margin of a lateral ocellus or along anterior margin of the anterior ocellus.

label: ocular ocellar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is shortest and connects the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.

label: ocular sclerite
Defs: na

label: ocular suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the margin of compound eye and corresponds to the circumocular ridge.

label: odontoidea
Defs: na

label: ommatidium
Defs: One of the facets of the compound eye.

label: open coxal cavity
Defs: na

label: operculum
Defs: The sclerite that functions like a lid and covers the spiracular opening.

label: oral cavity
Defs: na

label: orbicula
Defs: The sclerite that is located proximodorsally on the pretarsus and connects the distodorsal margin of the telotarsus with the dorsal part of the arolium.

label: orbital band
Defs: The band that extends along the medial margin of the eye.

label: orbital carina
Defs: na

label: outer carina of the mandible
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends anteriorly on the lateral surface of the mandible.

label: outer groove
Defs: The impression that extends dorsally of the condylar carina of the mandible.

label: outer orbit
Defs: The line that extends along the border between the eye and gena.

label: ovipore
Defs: The anatomical space that receives sperm ejected from the aedeagus.

label: ovipositor
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first valvulae, second valvulae, third valvulae, first valvifers, second valvifers and female T9.

label: external female genitalia
Defs: The anatomical cluster that composed of the median oviduct, spermatheca and the ovipositor apparatus.

label: ovipositor sheath
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the third valvulae.

label: paddle shaped seta
Defs: The sensillum with a paddle-shaped cuticular componenet on the probasitarsus.

label: palpifer
Defs: The area that is located on the stipes and which articulates with the maxillary palp.

label: stipes
Defs: The appendage that is connected posteroproximally to the hypostoma, anteroproximally and lateroproximally to the mandible and medioproximally to the labium and the hypopharynx via conjunctiva, is connected to the cranium via muscles and that bears the maxillary palp.

label: paracoxal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the metapectus.

label: paracoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the paracoxal ridge.

label: paraglossa
Defs: The lobe that is connected to the distal margin of the prementum posteroproximally, to the premental hypopharynx proximolaterally and anteroproximally, to the glossa proximomedially and bears the basiparaglossal brush and the paraglossal sclerite.

label: premento-paraglossal muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises from the ventral part of the prementum, anterior to the origin of the premento-glossal muscle and ventral premento-salivarial muscle and inserts just distally of the distal margin of the prementum.

label: paramandibular process
Defs: The projection that is located distolaterally on the hypostoma and extends to the clypeus separating the mandibular socket from the oral foramen.

label: paraocular area
Defs: The area that is located on the face and delimited ventromedially by the epistomal sulcus.

label: paraocular carina
Defs: The carina that surrounds the compound eye.

label: paraocular lobe
Defs: The area that is located ventromedially on the paraocular area and is surrounded partly by the epistomal sulcus.

label: parapenis
Defs: The area that is the dorsomedian part of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the distodorsal and proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.

label: parapenisjugum
Defs: The area that is narrow and connects the parapenis with the rest of the gonostipes.

label: parapsidal line
Defs: The signum that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsoventral indirect flight muscle.

label: parapsis
Defs: The area that is delimited medially by the parapsidal line and laterally by the parascutal carina.

label: parascrobal area
Defs: The area that is located on the upper face, is delimited medially by the antennal scrobe and laterally by the inner orbit.

label: parascutal carina
Defs: The rim that extends along the lateral margin of the lateral area of the mesoscutum and delimits the preaxilla.

label: paravalva
Defs: The projection that is lateral and located apically on the penisvalva.

label: valviceps
Defs: The area that is the distal part of the penisvalva dorsally of the ergot.

label: parietal
Defs: The area that is lateral on the cranium between the frontal and occipital areas, separated above by the coronal suture.

label: parietal band
Defs: The band that is located on the anterior part of the larval head.

label: parossiculo-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal apex of the parossiculus and inserts on the medially on the penisvalva. The muscle inserts on the ergot if present.

label: parossiculo-phallotremal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that originates from the parossiculus and inserts on the endophallic membrane around the phallotrema.

label: patch
Defs: The area that is round and differs from surrounding regions in sculpture, setae, and/or pigmentation.

label: pedicel
Defs: The antennal segment that is connected proximally to the scape and distally to the flagellum.

label: penisvalvo-endophallal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the median surface of the proximal apex of the penisvalva and inserts on the endophallus.

label: penisvalvo-gonossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonossiculal muscle that arises from the penisvalva.

label: penisvalvo-phallotremal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the medial surface of the proximal part of the penisvalva and inserts on the endophallus just around the phallotrema.

label: peristome
Defs: The anatomical cluster that comprises the ventral marginal of the cranium, including the clypeus, the pleurostomata, and the hyperstomata.

label: peritreme
Defs: A sclerotic ring surrounding the outer spiracular opening.

label: phallotrema
Defs: The anatomical space that is the distal opening of the endophallus.

label: pharate adult
Defs: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

label: pile
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of fine, dense setae, acanthae or microtrichiae.

label: planta
Defs: The sclerite that is located proximoventrally on the pretarsus and is connected proximally with the unguitractor plate and distally with the arolium.

label: pleural apophysis
Defs: The apophysis that is adjacent to the pleural ridge.

label: pleural area
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of the pro-, meso-, and metapleura.

label: pleural wing process
Defs: The fossa that is located on the dorsal margin of the pleuron and accommodates the second axillary sclerite.

label: pleurite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the pleuron.

label: pleuro-ventral line
Defs: The line of separation between the pleural region and the venter, lying mesad of the limb bases, but obscured when the latter are fused with the sterna.

label: pleurostoma
Defs: The area that extends on the ventral (anterior) margin of the cranium along the site of origin of the conjunctiva connecting the mandible with the cranium and is delimited posteriorly (ventrally) by the posterior (ventral) margin of the pleurostomal fossa and anteriorly (dorsally) by the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostomal condyle and laterally by the mouth margin.

label: pleurostomal condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostoma and inserts into the mandibular acetabulum.

label: pleurostomal fossa
Defs: The fossa that is located postero- (ventro-) medially on the pleurostoma and accommodates the mandibular condyle.

label: pleurostomal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends between the pleurostomal fossa and pleurostomal condyle and delimits the lateral margin of the pleurostoma.

label: pleurostomal suture
Defs: The suture that is dorsal to the mandible and is part of the subgenal suture.

label: plica
Defs: The carina that arises from the anterior margin of the abdominal tergum 1 medially of the propodeal spiracle extends to the posterior propodeal projection.

label: plica basalis
Defs: The wing fold that is located between the mediocubital field and axillary region.

label: plica vannalis
Defs: The wing fold that is located between the cubital field and the first vannal vein.

label: plical area
Defs: The area that is delimited laterally by the metapleural carina and medially by the plica.

label: propodeum
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located posterior to the metapleural carina.

label: pollex
Defs: The area corresponding to the upper margin of the mandible, above the acetabular groove, commonly ending in the preapical tooth or teeth.

label: postacetabular patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located ventrally on the mesopleuron posterior to the epicnemial carina.

label: postacetabular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends posteriorly along the epicnemial carina.

label: postalar process
Defs: The process that is located anterolaterally on the mesoscutellar-axillar complex and separates the site of origin of the fore wing from the site of origin of the hind wing.

label: postclypeus
Defs: The area that is located on the clypeus and is delimited by the epistomal sulcus and a medial transverse anatomical line.

label: postcubitus
Defs: The usual sixth vein of the wing, associated basally with the cubitus.

label: anterior cranio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The mandibular muscle that arises posterodorsally from the cranium and inserts on the tendon attached anteroproximally on the mandible.

label: posterior extension of preaxilla
Defs: The area that is located on the posteroventral corner of the preaxilla and articulates with the anterior extension of the lateral axillar area.

label: posterior glossal plate
Defs: The area that is delimited laterally distally and proximally by the sclerites that are connected to the distal margin of the prementum and receive the site of insertion of the premento-paraglossal muscle.

label: posterior glossal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite of the posterior glossal plate that is paired.

label: posterior labral retractor
Defs: The labral muscle that arises from the upper face laterally to the anterior fronto-labral muscle and inserts on the torma.

label: torma
Defs: The process that is located on the proximolateral corner of the labrum. The torma corresponds to the site of attachment for the posterior fronto-labral muscle.

label: posterior lingual plate
Defs: na

label: posterior mesepimeral area
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the mesepimeral sulcus.

label: posterior mesepimeral inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the mesepimeron, posteriorly of the subalar pit to the coxal articulation.

label: posterior mesofurco-mesolaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The mesolaterophragmal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesolaterophragma posterior to the site of origin of the anterior mesofuco-mesolaterophragmal muscle.

label: posterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the dorsal axillar area, posteriorly of the site of origin of the anterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle (if present) and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the mesotrochanter.

label: posterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle
Defs: The mesofurcal muscle that originates proximally from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesopleuron.

label: posterior mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
Defs: na

label: posterior mesoscutellar sulcus
Defs: The line that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum and corresponds to the posterior mesoscutellar ridge.

label: posterior notal wing process
Defs: The articular process that is located on the lateral margin of the alinotum and articulates with the first axillary sclerite.

label: posterior ocellar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the margin of the lateral ocelli.

label: posterior profurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends along the dorsal margin of the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral profurco-procoxal muscle.

label: posterior pronotal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the pronotum and articulates with the anterior mesopleural inflection.

label: posterior pronotal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends parallel with the posterior margin of the pronotum and corresponds to the ridge of the posterior pronotal inflection.

label: posterior propodeal projection
Defs: The propodeal spine that is located posteromedially of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: propodeal spine
Defs: The spine on the metapectal-propodeal complex that is paired and is medial to the propodeal spiracle.

label: posterior scutellar depression
Defs: The line that extends just posterior of the posterior mesoscutellar ridge/mesoscutellar arms and delimits the posterior margin of the mesoscutellar pulsatory organ and the anterior margin of the mesopostscutellum.

label: posterior scutum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the mesoscutum.

label: posterior subalar pit
Defs: na

label: posterior supraalar area
Defs: The area that is limited medially by the transmetanotal carina and bears the postmedian metanotal wing process.

label: posterior tentorial pit
Defs: The tentorial pit that corresponds to posterior tentorial arm.

label: posterior thoracic spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that is located dorsally on the border between the mesopectus and the metapectus.

label: posterodorsal edge of pronotum
Defs: The edge that is located at the intersection of the dorsal and lateral margins of the pronotum.

label: posterodorsal edge of the mesopleuron
Defs: The edge that is located at the intersection of the mesepimeral ridge and the inflected dorsal margin of the mesopleuron.

label: posterolateral pronotal area
Defs: The area that is limited anteriorly by the posterolateral pronotal sulcus.

label: posterolateral pronotal carina
Defs: The carina that extends parallel to the posterolateral margin of the pronotum and delimits the posterolateral margin of pronotum.

label: posterolateral pronotal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that arises from the ventrolateral pit of the pronotum and reaches the posterolateral carina of the pronotum ventral to the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: posteroventral metapleural pit
Defs: The pit that corresponds to the dilator muscle apodeme.

label: postgena
Defs: The area that is located on the occiput ventrally of the occipital foramen.

label: postgenal cushion
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the postgena.

label: postgenal pit
Defs: The pit that corresponds to the ventral-most point of the posterior site of fusion of the ventral lamella of the tentorium.

label: postgenal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds with the postgenal ridge.

label: postgenal suture
Defs: The groove that is median, vertical and extends between the occipital and oral foramina separating the postgenae.

label: postlabium
Defs: na

label: postmarginal vein
Defs: The abscissa that is marginal and located distal to the marginal vein.

label: postmedian notal wing process
Defs: The fossa that is located on the lateral axillar area and articulates with the posterior end of the first axillary sclerite of the fore wing.

label: postmentum
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that are on the postmental area.

label: postoccipital ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds to the postoccipital sulcus.

label: postoccipital sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is located on the postoccipital suture.

label: postoccipital suture
Defs: The line that delimits the postocciput from the cranium.

label: postocellar furrow
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the posterior margin of the lateral ocelli.

label: postocellar vertex
Defs: The area posterior to the imaginary line intersecting the lateral ocelli and anterior to the occipital carina.

label: postorbital carina
Defs: The carina that extends posteriorly from the genal sulcus.

label: postpectal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits anterolaterally the mesocoxal depression.

label: postphragma
Defs: The phragma that is located posteriorly on a thoracic segment.

label: poststernite
Defs: The area corresponding to the postcostal lip of a definitive sternal plate that includes the intersegmental sclerotization following.

label: posttergite
Defs: The area that corresponds to the narrow postcostal lip of a postnotal thoracic plate.

label: preapical tooth
Defs: The tooth that is located distodorsally on the mandible.

label: mandibular tooth
Defs: The projection that is located distally on the mandible.

label: prearticular incisure
Defs: The notch that is located on the margin of the second valvifer immediately anterior to the basal articulation of the second valvulae.

label: second valvula
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is distal to the basal articulation and to the processus musculares and is limited medially by the median body axis.

label: preaxillar carina
Defs: The carina that extends across the preaxilla and separates the articulation area for the tegula.

label: prelabium
Defs: na

label: postmento-premental muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that is unpaired, arises from the postmentum and inserts on the proximal margin of the prementum.

label: preoccipital carina
Defs: The carina that is transverse and extends posteriorly of the lateral ocelli and compound eye and delimits anteriorly the preoccipital lunula.

label: preoccipital furrow
Defs: The sulcus that arises medially from the anterior margin of the occipital carina and extends towards the anterior ocellus.

label: preoccipital lunula
Defs: The area that is concave, is located on the vertex and is limited anteriorly by the preoccipital carina and posteriorly by the occipital carina.

label: preocellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located on upper face adjacent the anterior margin of the median ocellus and corresponds internally to a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

label: preorbital carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the face, parallels the inner orbit and is paired.

label: prepectus
Defs: The intersegmentalia that is located on the mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle.

label: prescutal ridge
Defs: The ridge that seperates the prescutum from scutum.

label: prescutal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that sets off the prescutum from the scutum and corresponds to the prescutal ridge.

label: prescutum
Defs: The area that is located on the alinotum and is limited by the antecostal suture and prescutal suture.

label: prespecular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the speculum and corresponds to the anterior margin of the speculum.

label: prespiracular propodeal area
Defs: The area that is located between the first metasomal spiracle and metapleural arm and delimited laterally by the metapleural carina.

label: presternum
Defs: The area that is located on the basisternum and is delimited by the sternacostal sulcus.

label: prestigma
Defs: The patch that is enlarged, sclerotized, and located at the apex of one or more wing veins on the anterior margin of the wing.

label: primary gonopore
Defs: The anatomical space that is the transition from the ductus ejaculatorius to the endophallus and therefore the transition from the internal to the external male genitalia.

label: prodiscrimen
Defs: The discrimen that is located in the prothorax and corresponds to the prodiscrimenal lamella.

label: prosternum
Defs: The sclerite that is connected posteriorly to the propleuron and bears the prodiscrimen and the profurca.

label: prodiscrimenal lamella
Defs: The discrimenal lamella that is located in the prothorax.

label: profurcal arm
Defs: The sternal apophysis that is paired, arises from the furcasternum of the prothorax and continuous with the prodiscrimenal lamella.

label: profurcal pit
Defs: The furcal pit that is located in the prothorax.

label: profurco-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the anterior surface of the dorsal profurcal lamella.

label: laterocervical muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the laterocervicalia.

label: pronope
Defs: The depression that is dorsomedian and is located on the pronotum.

label: pronotal cervical sulcus
Defs: na

label: pronotal collar
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is subhorizontal and located posteriorly of the pronotal neck.

label: pronotal cushion
Defs: The setiferous patch that corresponds with the transverse sulcus of the pronotum.

label: pronotal flange
Defs: The evagination that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the head-propectus articulation.

label: cuticular evagination
Defs: The area that is evaginated.

label: pronotal groove
Defs: na

label: pronotal lobe
Defs: The area that is located dorsally on the posterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: pronotal plate
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is median, raised and limited laterally by sharp edges.

label: pronotal projection
Defs: The projection that is part of the pronotum.

label: pronotal shoulder
Defs: The corner that is located anterolaterally on the horizontal part of the collar.

label: pronotal side
Defs: The area that is located on the pronotum and that is vertical.
