label: pronotal suprahumeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and delimits the dorsal pronotal area.

label: pronotal verricule
Defs: The verricule that is located on the anterosubmedial pronotum.

label: verricule
Defs: The setiferous patch that is composed of closely gathered setae.

label: pronoto-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the pronotum and insert on the cervical apodeme.

label: pronoto-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that originates from the posterolateral part of the pronotum and inserts on the mesobasalare.

label: pronoto-anterior thoracic spiracle muscle
Defs: The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that arises from the pronotum.

label: anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: pronoto-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the pronotum and inserts on the postocciput.

label: pronoto-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the pronotum and inserts on the posterolateral margin of the procoxa.

label: pronoto-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that arises along the ventral margin of the pronotum, and inserts laterally on the profurca.

label: pronoto-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that originates medially from the pronotum and inserts submedially on the prophragma.

label: prophragmal muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts on the prophragma.

label: pronoto-propleural muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises medially from the pronotum and inserts on the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron.

label: pronoto-third axillary sclerite muscle
Defs: na

label: propectus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the prosternum and the propleuron.

label: propleural arm
Defs: The apodeme that is located on the posterodorsal corner of the lateral propleural area and corresponds to the site of muscle attachment.

label: propleural cervical sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the propleuron.

label: propleural epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The epicoxal sulcus that sets of the epicoxal lobe from the ventral part of the ventral propleural area.

label: propleuro-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleuron and inserts on the postocciput.

label: propleuro-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from along the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron and inserts on the procoxa.

label: propleuro-protrochanteral muscle
Defs: The protrochanteral muscle that arises from the propleuron and inserts on the protrochanteral apodeme.

label: protrochanteral muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the protrochanter.

label: protrochanter
Defs: The trochanter that is located on the fore leg.

label: propodeal bridge
Defs: The area that is located between the propodeal foramen and metacoxal foramina.

label: propodeal foramen
Defs: The foramen that is located on the metapectal-propodeal complex in which the petiole is positioned.

label: propodeal tooth
Defs: The articular process that is located on the margin of the propodeal-metapectal complex around the propodeal foramen and bears the metasomal condyle of the propodeum.

label: propodeo-first metasomal spiracle muscle
Defs: na

label: propodeo-second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal sternal muscle that originates ventral to the metaphragma and inserts on the anterodorsal margin of the abdominal sternite 2.

label: propodeo-second abdominal segment muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the propodeum and inserts laterally on the second abdominal segment.

label: propodeo-second abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the abdominal tergum 1 and inserts on the abdominal tergum 2.

label: prospinasterno-mesofurcal muscle
Defs: The mesofurcal muscle that arises from the prospinasternum and inserts on the mesofurca.

label: prospinasternum
Defs: The spinasternum that is located anterior to the mesopectus.

label: prosternal incision
Defs: The notch that separates the basisternum from the furcasternum in the prosternum.

label: prosterno-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the prosternum and inserts on the procoxa.

label: tibial spur
Defs: The spur that is located distally on a tibia.

label: proximal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle-parossiculal muscle that arises proximally from the lateral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the proximal part of the parossiculus.

label: proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The dorsal gonostyle/volsella complex penisvalval muscle that arises proximodorsally from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts on the penisvalva distally of the site of insertion of the distodorsal gononstyle/volsella complex-penisvalva muscle.

label: proximolateral apodeme of cupula
Defs: The apodeme that is located laterally on the proximal margin of the cupula and corresponds to the site of insertion of the second lateral 9th sterno-cupulal muscle.

label: proximoventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle/volsella complex, inserts on the proximal end of the penisvalva and is oriented proximodorsally.

label: pseudoceps
Defs: The projection that is medial and located apically on the penisvalva.

label: pseudophragma
Defs: The flange that extends along the dorsal margin of the dorsal mesopostnotal flange.

label: pulvillum
Defs: na

label: pygidial plate
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the tergum of the last externally visible segment of the abdomen.

label: radial vein
Defs: The wing vein that is connected to the second axillary sclerite and extends posterior to the subcosta.

label: radicle
Defs: The area that is located proximally on the scape, is limited distally by a constriction and bears proximally the basal knob.

label: radio-medial cross vein
Defs: The wing vein that connects the radial vein with the medial vein.

label: ramal rod
Defs: The area that extends external to the dorsal ramus of the first valvula.

label: rami valvularum
Defs: The area that is located proximally on valvulae and is connected to the valvifers.

label: region
Defs: na

label: remigial region
Defs: The wing region anterior to the vannal fold containing the costa, subcosta, radius, medius, cubitus, and postcubitus.

label: retractor of the epipharynx
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that arises from the clypeus and inserts on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: retractor of the mouth angle
Defs: The hypopharyngeal muscle that arises from the upper face and inserts on the proximolateral process of the sitophore.

label: rhachis
Defs: The ridge that extends along the ventral surface of the second valvula that is partially enclosed by the aulax.

label: ruga
Defs: The carina that is irregularly non-linear.

label: salivarial orifice
Defs: The anatomical space that is situated posteriorly in the salivarium, proximal to the insertion of the dilatators.

label: salivarium
Defs: The area that is adjacent to the proximal end of the salivary duct and corresponds to the site of insertion of the dorsal and ventral premento-salivarial muscles.

label: salivary duct
Defs: The duct that leads from the salivary gland.

label: scale
Defs: The sensillum with a scale-like cuticular component.

label: scopa
Defs: The setiferous patch that is used for pollen storage.

label: scrobal depression
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of antennal scrobes.

label: sculpture
Defs: The area that is located on the sclerite and that is composed of repetitive anatomical structures.

label: scutellar bridge
Defs: The apodeme that originates from the scutoscutellar ridge and fuses with the posterior part of the mesoscutellum.

label: scutellar fovea
Defs: The depression that is medially located on the scutoscutellar suture.

label: scutellar sulcus
Defs: na

label: scutoscutellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the mesoscutellum and corresponds to the scutoscutellar suture.

label: scutoscutellar sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the scutoscutellar suture.

label: scutoscutellar suture
Defs: The line that traverses the mesonotum between the postmedian notal wing processes.

label: second axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that articulates ventrally with the pleuron and medially with the first axillary sclerite, posteriorly with the third axillary sclerite and is connected with the base of the radial vein.

label: second dorsal diagonal muscle
Defs: na

label: second median plate
Defs: The sclerite that is located at the base of the mediocubital field, folding convexly on the outer edge of the first median plate along the plica basalis.

label: second mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The mesonotal muscle that arises medially from mesopleuron and inserts on the ventral surface of the lateral axillar area.

label: second phragmo-third phragmal muscle
Defs: The metaphragmal muscle that arises from the mesophragma and inserts on the metaphragma.

label: metaphragmal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metaphragma.

label: proximal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle that inserts on the median wall of the harpe and arises proximally of the site of origin of the distal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle.

label: second valvifer
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is proximal to the basal articulation and to the processus musculares and articulates with female T9.

label: second valvifer-third valvula complex
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is proximal to the basal articulation.

label: second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex
Defs: The area that is connected to the ninth tergite and the first valvifer via conjunctiva, is articulated to the first tergite, and bears the aulax.

label: sensillar patch
Defs: The patch that differs from surrounding region by presence of sensilla.

label: sensillar patch of the male flagellomere
Defs: The sensillar patch that is located on the ventral surface of the male flagellomere.

label: sensillum trichodeum curvatum
Defs: The sensillum that is curved.

label: sex flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is modified and located on a male organism.

label: skaphion
Defs: The area that is anteriorly on the mesonotum and delimited posteriorly by the skaphion carina.

label: skaphion carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the skaphion posteriorly.

label: spatha
Defs: The sclerite that is unpaired and located just dorsally of the basal part of the aedeagus in some Aculeata.

label: specialized adhesive spur
Defs: The spur that is located on the tibia and is adhesive.

label: spur
Defs: The process that is surrounded by conjunctiva and evaginated and that is basally sclerotized.

label: speculum
Defs: The area that is located dorsolaterally on the mesosoma, is delimited posteriorly by the mesepimeral ridge and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.

label: spermatheca
Defs: The pouch that accommodates the sperm.

label: pouch
Defs: The area that is located on the conjunctiva and invaginated.

label: spiculum
Defs: The apophysis that is located medially on the anterior margin of the abdominal sternum 9 and corresponds to the site of origin of the mediolateral S9-cupulal muscles.

label: spina
Defs: The apophysis that is located medially on the spinasternum.

label: spinasternum
Defs: The sclerite that is located anteriorly on the thoracic sternum and bears the spina.

label: spine
Defs: The process that lacks non-sclerotised ring at the base.

label: sternacostal suture
Defs: The suture that extends along the border of the basisternum and sternellum.

label: sternaulus
Defs: The line that marks the site of origin of the mesopleuro-basalare and first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: sternellum
Defs: The area that is located on the eusternum posteriorly of the site of origin of the furca.

label: sternite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the sternum.

label: stigma
Defs: The patch on the wing that is sclerotized and is on the anterior margin of the fore wing.

label: stylet
Defs: na

label: subalar area
Defs: The area that is delimited by the mesepimeral inflection and corresponding subalar ridge and bears the mesopleural wing process.

label: subalar pit
Defs: The pit that is located posterodorsally on the mesopectus corresponds to the posterodorsal edge of the mesopleuron.

label: hypoproct
Defs: The area that is located in between the anal opening and the genitalia.

label: subantennal area
Defs: The area that is located ventrally of the antennal rim and is delimited by the subantennal grooves and the epistomal sulcus.

label: subantennal groove
Defs: The impression that is located on the face ventrally of the antennal foramen and dorsally of the clypeus.

label: subaxillular bar
Defs: The area that is elevated, located on the lateroventral margin of the mesoscutellar axillar complex and is continuous anteriorly with the postalar process.

label: subcosta
Defs: The wing vein that is connected to the first axillary sclerite and extends posterior to the costa.

label: subgenal carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the cranium, ventrally of the gena and extending from the hypostomal carina to the facial articulation of the mandible.

label: subgenal coronet
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the carina paramandibular process and curves behind the mandibular base.

label: submarginal carina of abdominal tergite
Defs: The carina that extends laterally on the abdominal tergite.

label: tergite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the tergum.

label: submarginal groove
Defs: The impression extends along the lateral margin of the metasomal mediotergite.

label: mediotergite
Defs: The tergite that is located medially on the tergum.

label: submarginal vein
Defs: Basal-most portion of the forewing vein complex that occurs behind the costal cell; measured from the constriction that delimits the humeral plate to the point at which the vein touches the leading edge of the wing apically.

label: submedian carina
Defs: The carina that arises from the anterior mandibular articulation that is located medially of the orbital carina and laterally of the frontal carina.

label: submetapleural carina
Defs: The carina that is located along the ventral metapleural margin, between the mesocoxal foramen and metacoxal foramen.

label: subpleural signum
Defs: The signum that is located submedially on the ventral face of the mesopleuron. The subpleural signum corresponds to the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal (pl2-t2a) muscle.

label: subpleuron
Defs: The area that is located ventrally on the pectus.

label: sucking pump
Defs: na

label: supraalar area
Defs: The area that is located laterally of the longitudinal metanotal carina.

label: epiproct
Defs: The sclerite that is located dorsally of the anal opening.

label: suture
Defs: The line that marks the fusion of two ancestral sclerites.

label: synsternal setiferous patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the synsternum.

label: synsternum
Defs: The sternite that is at least two times as long as an adjacent sternite.

label: synsternal translucent patch
Defs: The translucent patch that is located on the synsternite.

label: translucent patch
Defs: The patch that is less melanized than the surrounding area and is translucent.

label: syntergal translucent patch
Defs: The translucent patch that is located submedially on the syntergum.

label: tarsal claw
Defs: The spur that is curved and projects from the apex of the last tarsal segment on either side of the arolium of the pretarsus.

label: fore wing tegula
Defs: The cuticular evagination that is located laterally of the preaxilla and obscures the anterior mesonoto-first axillary articulation and the mesopleuro-second axillary sclerite joints.

label: telotarsus
Defs: The tarsomere that is apical.

label: temple
Defs: The area that is located on the gena, posterior to the compound eye.

label: tendon
Defs: The portion of tissue that is fibrous, strong, composed of tendon cells and connects the muscle to the integument.

label: tentorium
Defs: The apodeme that has its sites of origin marked by the anterior and posterior tentorial pits and gular sulci.

label: tentorial bridge
Defs: The apodeme that connects medially the tentorial arms.

label: tentorio-antennal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the dorsal surface of the anterior broadened part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts on the scape.

label: tentorio-stipital muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises on the posteroventral part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts on the median wall of the stipes.

label: maxillar muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the maxilla.

label: terebra
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first and second valvulae.

label: testis
Defs: The gonad that is consisting of testis follicles, is connected with the vas deferens and seminal vesicle.

label: third axillary
Defs: The axillary sclerite that corresponds to the site of insertion of the mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite muscles and is connected proximally with the fourth axillary sclerite.

label: third mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The mesonotal muscle that originates from the ventral apodeme of the first phragma and inserts on the acropleural apodeme of the mesopleuron.

label: third phragmo-second abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the metaphragma and inserts on the dorsal surface of the second abdominal tergum.

label: second abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the second abdominal tergum.

label: third valvula
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-third valvula complex that is posterior to the distal vertical conjunctiva of the second valvifer-third valvula complex.

label: thyridium
Defs: The patch that is located on the gastrocoelus and has specialized sculpture.

label: torular space
Defs: The area that is located between the antennal rims.

label: torular triangle
Defs: The area that is delimited by the ventrally bifurcating central keel.

label: torulus
Defs: The foramen that is located on the head in which the radicle is positioned.

label: transaxillar carina
Defs: The carina that divides the dorsal axillar area into horizontal and vertical areas.

label: transmetanotal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the supraalar area posteriorly.

label: transpleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends from the mesopleural pit to the mesocoxal articulation.

label: transscutal fissure
Defs: The line that traverses the mesoscutum and originates from the lateral margin between the antemedian and postmedian notal wing processes.

label: transscutal line
Defs: na

label: transverse carina on petiole
Defs: The carina that delimits the anterior vertical area of abdominal segment 2.

label: transverse epipharyngeal muscle
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that extends between the lateral parts of the sitophore.

label: transverse pronotal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the pronotal neck.

label: transverse pronotal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the anteromedian pronotal ridge.

label: trochantellus
Defs: The area that is located proximally on the femur and is delimited by a groove.

label: trochanter
Defs: The leg segment that is located proximal to the femur and distal to the coxa.

label: tubercle
Defs: The process that is small and knob-like or round.

label: tuberculate verricule
Defs: The verricule that arises from a tubercle.

label: type I sensillum trichodea
Defs: Sensilla trichodea type I occur on the distal ends [...] of the antennal flagellum.  They have small conical basal sockets with slender and strongly bent shafts.

label: mechanosensory hair
Defs: The aporous sensillum that has a hairlike cuticular component.

label: aporous sensillum

label: abdominal laterotergite 5
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 5.

label: abdominal laterotergite 10
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 10.

label: abdominal laterotergite 6
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 6.

label: abdominal laterotergite 7
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 7.

label: abdominal laterotergite 9
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 9.

label: abdominal mediotergite 1
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 1.

label: abdominal mediotergite 10
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 10.

label: intertarsomeral joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of two tarsomeres.

label: abdominal mediotergite 7
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 7.

label: abdominal mediotergite 8
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 8.

label: abdominal mediotergite 9
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 9.

label: dilator muscle of the 5th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 5 and inserts on the 5th abdominal spiracle.

label: dilator muscle of the 4th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 4 and inserts on the 4th abdominal spiracle.

label: 4th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 4.

label: dilator muscle of the 3rd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 3 and inserts on the 3rd abdominal spiracle.

label: dilator muscle of the 2nd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises laterally from the abdominal sternum 2 and inserts on the 2nd abdominal spiracle.

label: 2nd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located on the abdominal segment 2.

label: cup-shaped socket on pleuron
Defs: The projection that is located posteriorly on the subalar area and accommodate the posterior end of the second axillary sclerite of the fore wing at the beginning of the upstroke of the wing.

label: corbicula
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed by the concave lateral (external, anterior) area of the metatibia and two rows of setae extending along the lateral margins of the area.

label: basitarsal articular process of the protibia
Defs: The articular process that is located distodorsally on the protibia and bears the basitarsal fossa of the protiba.

label: basitarsal fossa of the metatibia
Defs: The fossa that is located on the basitarsal articular process of the metatibia and accommodates the tibial condyle of the metabasitarsus.

label: basitarsal articular process of the mesotibia
Defs: The articular process that is located distodorsally on the mesotibia and bears the basitarsal fossa of the protiba.

label: basitarsal fossa of the mesotibia
Defs: The fossa that is located on the basitarsal articular process of the mesotibia and accommodates the tibial condyle of the mesobasitarsus.

label: axillar phragma
Defs: The apodeme that is located submedially on the anterior part of dorsal axillar surface and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle.

label: auricle
Defs: The area that is located laterally (dorsally, externally) on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus and accommodates the rastellum.

label: dilator muscle of the 6th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral spiracular apodeme of the abdominal sternum 6 and inserts on the 6th abdominal spiracle.

label: pollen press
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the auricle and the rastellum.

label: articular membrane of the protibio-probasitarsal joint
Defs: The articular membrane that is located in the protibio-probasitarsal joint.

label: articular membrane of the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint
Defs: The articular membrane that is located in the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint.

label: arcus
Defs: The sclerite that encircles ventrolaterally the proximal part of the arolium.

label: anteromesoscutum
Defs: The area that is located anterior to the transscutal articulation.

label: anterolateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle that arises anterolaterally from the metapectus.

label: anterolateral metacoxo-metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The metatrochanteral muscle that arises anteriorly from the metacoxa and inserts on the articular membrane of the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint laterally of the anterior metacoxo-metatrochanteral articulation.

label: anterolateral mesopectal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the anterior margin of the mesopectus and articulates with the posterior pronotal inflection.

label: anterior trochanteral fossa of the mesocoxa
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the mesocoxa accommodating the anterior coxal condyle of the mesotrochanter.

label: anterior trochanteral articular process of the procoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the procoxa and bears the anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa.

label: anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior trochanteral articular process of the procoxa and inserts on the anterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter.

label: anterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the metacoxa and bears the anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: anterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior trochanteral articular process of the mesocoxa.

label: anterior mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the anterior coxal fossa of the mesotrochanter and the anterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa.

label: anterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the protrochanter accommodating the anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa.

label: anterior coxal fossa of the metatrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the metatrochanter and accommodates the anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa and inserts into the anterior coxal fossa of the metacoxa.

label: dilator muscle of the 7th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 7 and inserts on the 7th abdominal spiracle.

label: dilator muscle of the 8th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises anteroventrally from the tergal spiracular plate and inserts on the 8th abdominal spiracle.

label: dilator of the propodeal spiracle muscle
Defs: The first abdominal tergal spiracle muscle that does not extend between the dorsal and ventral spiraclar apodeme but attaches to one of these apodemes.

label: distal fossa of the tarsomere
Defs: The fossa that is located distodorsally on the tarsomere and accommodates the proximal condyle of the subsequent tarsomere.

label: dorsal metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle that arises dorsolaterally from the mesopleuron dorsally of the vantral metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle.

label: syntergum
Defs: The syntergum that is the posteriormost sclerite on the dorsum of the abdomen.

label: episternal foveae
Defs: The row of impressions that is located on the anteroventral edge of the mesopleuron and is correspond to the site of origin of the mesopleuro-mesobasalar muscle.

label: epistomal line
Defs: The line that extends between the anterior tentorial pits.

label: femoral articular process of the metatrochanter
Defs: The articular process that is located laterally on the distal margin of the metatrochanter and bears the femoral condyle of the metatrochanter.

label: femoral articular process of the protrochanter
Defs: The articular process that is located laterally on the distal margin of the protrochanter and bears the femoral condyle of the metatrochanter.

label: femoral condyle of the protibia
Defs: The femoral condyle of the tibia that is located on the protibia.

label: femoral condyle of the tibia
Defs: The condyle that is located proximally on the tibia and inserts into the tibial fossa of the femur.

label: femoral fossa of the metatrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located posteromedially on the metatrochanter and accommodates the trochanteral condyle of the metafemur.

label: first mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
Defs: The fore wing third axillary muscle that arises anterodorsally from the mesopleuron.

label: retinaculum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the fore wing, is ventrally curved and accommodate the hamuli.

label: humeral complex of the fore wing
Defs: The humeral complex that is located on the fore wing.

label: genuflexor plate of the mid leg
Defs: The genuflexor plate that is located in the mid leg.

label: genuflexor plate
Defs: The sclerite that is located posteriorly along the proximal margin of the tibia and corresponds to the site of insertion of the posterior femoro-tibial muscle.

label: genuflexor plate of the hind leg
Defs: The genuflexor plate that is located in the hind leg.

label: genuflexor plate of the fore leg
Defs: The genuflexor plate that is located in the fore leg.

label: frontal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is transverse and extends just ventrally of the median ocellus and is never connected to the scrobal sulcus or depression or interantennal area.

label: abdominal sternum 8
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 8.

label: inner orbit
Defs: The area that is delimited by the inner margin of compound eye, the preorbital suture and the supraorbital trabecula.

label: frontal carina
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the intertorular area (median margin of the antennal foramen) towards the vertex.

label: basitarsal fossa of the protibia
Defs: The fossa that is located on the basitarsal articular process of the protibia and accommodate the tibial condyle of the probasitarsus.

label: articular membrane of the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint
Defs: The  articular membrane that is located in the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint.

label: supraorbital suture
Defs: The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the supraorbital trabecula.

label: supraorbital trabecula
Defs: The bar that is adjacent to and parallel with the upper margin of each eye, which anteriorly terminates at the juncture of the transverse trabecula and preorbital trabecula.

label: surcoxal depression
Defs: The depression that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus anterior of the precoxal carina.

label: pronoto-propleural arm muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that originates from the pronotum and inserts on the propleural arm.

label: lateral pronoto-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that arises laterally of the site of origin of the median pronoto-prophragmal and medially of the site of origin of the lateral pronoto-postoccipital muscles.

label: median pronoto-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that arises medially of the site of origin of the lateral pronoto-prophragmal muscle.

label: adipose system
Defs: An organ system pertaining to fat.

label: organ system
Defs: A division of the whole organism into specialized systems.

label: alary muscle
Defs: The muscle that is attached to the dorsal vessel.

label: chorion
Defs: A hard shell external to the vitelline membrane of the egg.

label: laminated bridge
Defs: The area that is located proximally on the notal membrane near the processus articularis is sclerotised and is continuous with the second valvulae.

label: notal membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the medial margins of the second valvulae.

label: labral apodeme
Defs: The tendon that connects the fronto-labral muscle with the lateral margin of the labrum.

label: knee
Defs: The anatomical cluster that consists of the distal part of the femur and the proximal part of the tibia.

label: intrinsic muscle of the propleuron
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises from the propleuron.

label: intrinsic muscle of the metapleuron
Defs: The metapleural muscle that arises from the metapleuron.

label: metapleural muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metapleuron.

label: intrinsic muscle of the mesopleuron
Defs: The mesopleural muscle that arises from the mesopleuron.

label: mesopleural muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesopleuron.

label: intrinsic muscle of the harpe
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal margin of the lateral surface of the harpe and inserts proximally on the median surface of the harpe.

label: intrinsic maxillary palp muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that connects two maxillary sclerites.

label: intervalvifer articulation
Defs: The articulation between the first valvifer and second valvifer.

label: interorbital plane
Defs: The area that is defined by the anatomical lines that are tangent to a point at the minimal distance from the eyes to the lateral ocelli.

label: interocular separation
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the compound eyes on the vertex.

label: intermalar distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest horizontal diameter (major axis) of the oral foramen.

label: interarticular ridge of the first valvifer
Defs: The ridge that extends along the posterior margin of the first valvifer between the intervalvifer and tergovalvifer articulations.

label: infrabuccal pouch
Defs: The pouch that is situated on the hypopharyngeal wall distally of the sitophore.

label: inferior pronotal spine
Defs: The spine that is located laterally on the anterior margin of the pronotum.

label: hypopharyngeal lobe
Defs: The lobe that is situated distally of the sitophore and proximally of the infrabuccal pouch.

label: vertical epomia
Defs: The carina that is the vertical section of the epomial carina that begins ventrally and terminates at the junction of the transverse pronotal carina and the lateral epomia.

label: dorsal T9-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises along the posterodorsal part of the anterior margin of female T9 and inserts on the anterior section of the dorsal flanges of the second valvifer.

label: endite
Defs: The lobe that is situated distally on the maxilla and the labium medially of the palps.

label: dorsal T8-T9 muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that arises from the anteromedian margin of female T8 and inserts on the anteromedian margin of the female T9.

label: dorsal surface of the mesoscutellum
Defs: The area that surrounds the scutellar plate and differs from it in sculpture.

label: digital spine
Defs: The projection that is located apically on the gonossiculus.

label: distal hypopharynx
Defs: The area that is located on the anterior surface of the hypopharyngeal wall and is delimited proximally by the infrabuccal pouch or the distal margin of the sitophore, distally by the salivarial orifice and laterally by the lateral parts of the prementum and the hypopharyngeal rods.

label: dorsal aperture of the phallobase
Defs: The foramen that is located proximally on the cupula.

label: dorsal flange of the second valvifer
Defs: The flange that extends on the dorsal margin of the second valvifer. Part of the ventral T9-second valvifer muscle attaches to the flange.

label: dorsal pronoto-procoxal muscle
Defs: The pronoto-procoxal muscle that arises dorsomedially from the pronotum.

label: digestive system
Defs: The organ system involved in the absorption of nutrients.

label: metacoxo-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metacoxa.

label: mesocoxo-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesocoxa.

label: central nervous system
Defs: Collective name for all the nerve centers and their connective in the insect\'s body. In the context of Drosophila refers to the part of the nervous system consisting of the brain and ventral ganglia.

label: nervous system
Defs: The organ system that is composed of neurons and glial cells.

label: circulatory system
Defs: The anatomical system that is involved in circulation.

label: cordate apodeme
Defs: The apodeme on the anterior margin of female T9. The ventral T9-second valvifer muscle attaches partly on the apodeme.

label: lower mesepimeron
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesopleuro-mesosubalar muscle.

label: macrotergite
Defs: The syntergum that is located posteriorly of the petiole.

label: malar carina
Defs: The malar distance that is a carina.

label: coxopleurite
Defs: The pleurite that extends ventrally of the anapleurite and dorsally of the coxa.

label: occipito-cardinal muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises medially from the occiput dorsally of the occipital foramen and inserts on the proximolateral part of the cardo.

label: occipito-lacinial muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises from the occiput and inserts on the proximal part of the lacinial lobe.

label: occlusor of posterior thoracic spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises form the mesopectus and inserts on the posterior thoracic spiracle.

label: ocellar hair patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that extends posteriorly or posterolaterally of the median ocellus.

label: vertexal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is horizontal and extends between the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.

label: preorbital suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the median margin of the preorbital trabecula.

label: orbital furrow
Defs: The impression that arises laterally from the antennal rim and extends along the inner margin of the compound eye.

label: ovipositor apparatus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the ovipositor, abdominal terga 8-10, abdominal sternum 7 and muscles connecting them.

label: paraclypeal margin
Defs: The edge that extends laterally of the pleurostoma.

label: parapsidal hair line of mesoscutum
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: parapsidal ridge
Defs: The carina that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: parapsidal furrow
Defs: The impression that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: paraspiracular carina
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the paraspiracular sulcus.

label: pars articulares
Defs: The articular surface that is situated on the anteriorly on the ventral margin of the second valvifer and forms the lateral part of the basal articulation.

label: acrosternite 3
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 3.

label: acrosternite 4
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 4.

label: acrosternite 2
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: acrosternite 5
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: acrosternite 6
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 6.

label: acrosternite 7
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 7.

label: acrosternite 8
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 8.

label: acrosternite 9
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: ventral pronoto-procoxal muscle
Defs: The pronoto-procoxal muscle that originates anteroventrally from the pronotum and inserts posterolaterally on the procoxa.

label: ventral T9-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the lateral region of female T9 and inserts along the posterior part of the dorsal flange of the second valvifer.

label: ventral plaque
Defs: The carina that is located ventrally on the scape and sensory in function.

label: venter
Defs: The area that is located between the left and right coxal foramina.

label: valvillus
Defs: The sclerite that articulates on the first valvula and projects into the egg/poison canal.

label: upper mesepisternum
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesopleuro-mesobasalar, second and third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing and second mesopleuro-mesonotal muscles.

label: trochantinal lobe
Defs: The area that is extends along the extreme posterior margin of the mesopleuron anterior to mesocoxa and is delimited anteriorly by an impression.

label: transverse suture
Defs: The impression that delimits anteriorly the transverse trabecula.

label: transscutal impression
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the transscutal line.

label: transoccipital suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the eyes posterior to the vertexal sulcus.

label: transepimeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that separates the upper mesepimeron from the lower mesepimeron.

label: transepimeral line
Defs: The line that corresponds to the ventral margin of the site of origin of the anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.

label: frenal carina
Defs: The frenal line that is a carina.

label: frenal sulcus
Defs: The frenal line that is a sulcus.

label: mesotrochantero-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesotrochanter.

label: third axillary sclerite
Defs: na

label: terminal spine
Defs: The spine that is located apically on the last clavomere.

label: tergosternal sulcus
Defs: A groove that is longitudinal and extends laterally on the petiole separating a dorsal and a ventral petiolar areas.

label: tergo-valvifer articulation
Defs: The articulation that is located between the female T9 and the first valvifer and is composed of the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the first valviferal fossa of the ninth tergite.

label: tentorio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The mandibular muscle arises ventrolaterally from the anterior part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts dorsomedially on the proximal part of mandible.

label: tentorio-cardinal muscle
Defs: The maxillary muscle that arises from the anterior region of the cranium and inserts adjacent to the cardino-stipital hinge.

label: T9-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the cordate apodeme and inserts dorsally on the proximal part of the genital membrane and on the opposite cordate apodeme.

label: genital membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the ventral margins of the second valvifers arching above the second valvula.

label: T8-first valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that originates from the lateral part of female T8 and inserts on the dorsal margin of the first valvifer.

label: female T8
Defs: The tergite that is connected to female T9 by muscles.

label: anterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises laterally from the metanotum, anterior to the site of origin of the posterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.

label: metanoto-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metanotum.

label: mesonoto-mesolaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The mesolaterophragmal muscle that arises from the mesonotum.

label: mesonoto-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the posterior margin of the mesocoxa.

label: mesonoto-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesonotum.

label: subsalivarial gland
Defs: The gland that is situated ventrally of the salivarium and empties into the salivarium.

label: mesosternal shelf
Defs: The area that is located ventrally on the mesopectus between the mesocoxal depression and the epicnemial carina.

label: subpetiolar process
Defs: The process that is located anteroventrally on the petiole.

label: subocular area
Defs: The area that is located between the malar sulcus and preorbital suture.

label: submetapleural ridge
Defs: The carina that extends from the ventral margin of the spiracular groove to the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: submedian groove
Defs: The line that is lobgitudinal and is located  closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: submedian carina of propodeum
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the propodeum.

label: sublateral groove
Defs: na

label: mediosternite
Defs: The sternite that is located medially on an abdominal sternum.

label: subglossal brush
Defs: The row of setae that is located laterally at the base of the glossa.

label: subcoxa
Defs: na

label: stylus of the third valvula
Defs: The sclerite that is connected to the distal end of the third valvula via conjunctiva.

label: dorsal valve
Defs: The area that is articulated with the right and left second valvifers at the basal articulation and bears the rhachises.

label: stridulatory organ
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the plectrum and the stridulitrum.

label: stipito-lacinial muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises along the lateral margin of the posterior stipital sclerite and inserts proximally on the median wall of the stipes just proximal to the lacinal lobe.

label: stipito-galeal muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises from the posterior sclerite of the stipes medial to the site of origin of the stipito-lacinial muscle and inserts on the median wall of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the stipito-lacinial muscle.

label: sternopleurite
Defs: The pleurite that located medially of the coxa and laterally of the sternum.

label: sternaular area
Defs: The area that is located between the epicnemial carina and the anterior margin of the femoral depression.

label: prospinasterno-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that arises form the prospinasternum.

label: paraspiracular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is longitudinal and extends posteriorly of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: spiracular groove
Defs: The impression that extends dorsally on the metapectal-propodeal complex from its anterior margin to the first abdominal spiracle.

label: speculum
Defs: The area that is smooth, located laterally of the frontal carina and is surrounded by sculptured regions of the upper face.

label: S7-first valvula muscle
Defs: The muscle that originates from the abdominal sternum 7 and inserts on the first valvula.

label: setal line
Defs: The row of setae that is located on the fore wing.

label: serrula
Defs: The notch that is located on the margin of sawtooth.

label: sawtooth
Defs: The process that is located along the ventral margin of the first valvula or the dorsal margin of the second valvula.

label: sensillar patch of the second valvifer
Defs: The patch that is composed of placoid sensilla adjacent to the intervalvifer articulation.

label: second valvifer-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises anteriorly from the dorsal flange of the second valvifer and inserts anteriorly on the dorsal part of the genital membrane.

label: second axillary sclerite of the fore wing
Defs: The second axillary sclerite  that is located on the mesothorax.

label: scutellar tubercular projection
Defs: The process that is located just medially of the margin of the scutellar plate.

label: glandular release pit of the scutellum
Defs: The area that is concave is located medially on the scutellar plate and corresponds to the opening of an exocrine gland.

label: scrobal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends dorsomedially from the upper median margin of the antennal rim.

label: scapular flange
Defs: The area that is set off from the lateral area of the mesoscutum by the anteriorly extended dorsal axillar area.

label: salivarial orifice
Defs: The anatomical space that is located on the boundary of the hypopharyngeal wall and the labium. The orifice is situated dorsally of the base of the glossa and corresponds to the opening for the salivarium.

label: metasterno-second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metadiscrimenal lamella.

label: second sterno-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the second abdominal sternum.

label: rod-like sensilla
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of rod-like sensilla and is located apically on the distal labial palp segment.

label: ramus
Defs: The process that is located on the funicular segment.

label: funicular segment
Defs: The flagellomere that is located in the funicle.

label: radix
Defs: The area that is located on the lateral wall of the first and second valvulae and is without annuli.

label: fore wing base
Defs: The wing base that is located in the mesothorax.

label: protuberance on malar space
Defs: The projection that is located ventrally on the malar space.

label: protibial apical pegs
Defs: The row of spurs that extends along the apical margin of the fore tibia.

label: propodeal areola
Defs: The area on the propodeum that is median and is delimited laterally by the median longitudinal carina.

label: mesofurco-propleural arm muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises form the mesofurca.

label: pronotal triangle
Defs: The area that is delimted by two pronotal ridges laterally and the posterior margin of the pronotum anteriorly.

label: pronotal ridge
Defs: The carina that delimits the pronotal plate posterolaterally.

label: pronotal disc
Defs: na

label: processus musculares
Defs: The apodeme that extends dorsally from the proximal part of the second valvula to the genital membrane and receives  the site of attachment of the posterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.

label: processus articularis
Defs: The process that extends laterally from the proximal part of the second valvula and forms the median part of the basal articulation, and corresponds to the site of attachment for the anterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.

label: dorsal ramus of the second valvula
Defs: The area that extends along the dorsal margin of the second valvula, bears the processus articularis anteriorly and the processus musculares on the antero-dorsal region and articulates anteriorly with the second valvifer via the basal articulation.

label: mesopleural suture
Defs: The pleural sulcus that is located on the mesopleuron.

label: mesopleuro-anterior thoracic spiracle muscle
Defs: The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that originates from the mesopleuron and inserts on the mesothoracic spiracle.

label: mesotarsal pegs
Defs: The row of spurs that extends laterally along the tarsomere of the mesotarsus.

label: mesothoracic venter
Defs: The area that is located ventrally of the mesopectus and limited dorsally by any line.

label: mesotibial apical peg
Defs: The row of spurs that extends along the distal margin of the mesotibia.

label: metalaterophragma
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the metaphragma.

label: metalaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metalaterophragma.

label: metanotal flange
Defs: The carina that is transverse and is located on the metascutellum.

label: metanoto-metatrochantinal muscle
Defs: The metatrochantinal muscle that arises form the metanotum.

label: metatrochantinal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metatrochantin.

label: metatrochantin
Defs: The trochantin that is located in the metathorax.

label: metasomal spiracle
Defs: The metasomal spiracle that is located on the metasomal tergum 7.

label: metasomal spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that is located on the metasoma.

label: mucro
Defs: The projection that is located distomedially on the hypopygium.

label: multiporous gustatory sensillum
Defs: The multiporous plate sensillum that is gustatory in function.

label: multiporous olfactory sensillum
Defs: The multiporous plate sensillum that is olfactory in function.

label: multiporous plate
Defs: The patch that is elevated, located on the flagellomere and is multiporous.

label: peduncle
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly on the petiole, delimited posteriorly by constriction and bears the propodeal fossa of the petiole.

label: petiolar flange
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly on the second metasomal sternum and overlaps ventrally the petiole.

label: prophragmo-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The laterocervical muscle that arises from the prophragma.

label: mesolaterophragmo-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metalaterophragma.

label: metalaterophragmo-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises from the metalaterophragma.

label: pharynx
Defs: The anatomical space that is located proximal to the cibarium.

label: posterior propleuro-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises posterodorsally from the propleuron.

label: second mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
Defs: The fore wing third axillary muscle that arises anteroventrally from the mesopleuron.

label: mesopleuro-mesosubalar muscle
Defs: The mesosubalare muscle that arises from the mesopleuron.

label: anterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises anteriorly of the site of origin of the posterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle.

label: posterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises posteriorly of the site of origin of the anterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle.

label: first valvifer-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the posterior part of the first valvifer and inserts anteriorly on the genital membrane anetrior to the T9-genital membrane muscle.

label: fore wing venation
Defs: The venation of the fore wing.

label: lateral mesofurco-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The mesofurco-metafurcal muscle that inserts on the anterior metafurcal arm.

label: lateral metafurco-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metafurco-metacoxal muscle that arises laterally from the metafurca.

label: median metafurco-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metafurco-metacoxal muscle that originates medially from the metafurca.

label: gastral tail
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the ovipositor and the distalmost abdominal tergum or the ovipositor and the distalmost abdominal tergum and the preceeding abdominal tergum.

label: genal carina
Defs: The carina that extends on the gena from the lateral margin of the oral foramen.

label: genal space
Defs: The area that is located between the genal carina and the posterior margin of the compound eye, bounded ventrally by the malar sulcus and dorsally by the vertex.

label: dorsal profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from along the dorsal profurcal lamella.

label: hairy lobe
Defs: The process that is setiferous and is located on the ventral margin of the second valvula and corresponds with one of the subdivisions of the second valvula.

label: hairy ring of the metasoma
Defs: The setiferous patch that extends along the second metasomal tergum.

label: lamnium
Defs: The area that is located on the lateral wall of the first and second valvulae and is subdivided by annuli.

label: lateral fovea
Defs: The area that is located medially on the transverse pronotal sulcus and separates the pronotal plate from the anterior rim of pronotum.

label: lateral frontal septum
Defs: The ridge that is paired, vertical and extends submedially on the frons. The posterior fronto-labral muscles arises partly from the septum.

label: epicuticle
Defs: The cuticle that does not contain chitin fibrils and is located externally of the exocuticle.

label: epipharyngeal brush
Defs: The setiferous patch that is unpaired, sublateral and situated distally on the epipharyngeal wall on the left torma.

label: ventral clypeal margin
Defs: The margin that delimits the clypeus distally (ventrally or anteriorly depending on the orientation of the head).

label: extrinsic muscle of the antenna
Defs: The muscle that arises from the tentorium and inserts proximally on the scape.

label: periepistomal striation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that composed of carinae radiating from the pleurostomal condyle.

label: first axillary sclerite of the fore wing
Defs: The first axillary sclerite that articulates anteriorly and medially with the anterior notal wing process laterally with the second axillary sclerite, and posteriorly with the posterior notal wing process.

label: preorbital trabecula
Defs: The bar that extends along the inner orbit and terminates dorsally at the juncture of the transverse trabecula and supraorbital trabecula.

label: profurco-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that arises from the profurca.

label: lateral scapo-pedicellar muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises posteromedially on the proximal part of the scape and inserts laterally on the proximal part of the pedicel.

label: lateral T8-T9 muscle
Defs: The ninth abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the anterolateral margin of female T8 and inserts on the anterolateral margin of female T9.

label: lateral tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises laterally from the proximal parts of the dorsal and anterior tentorial arms and is inserted posterolaterally on the proximal part of the scape.

label: laterodorsal projection of mesoscutellum
Defs: The process that is located posterodorsally on the axillular carina.

label: median bridge of the second valvifers
Defs: The area that connects posterodorsally the second valvifers and is the site of attachment for the posterior T9-second valvifer muscle.

label: median mesoscutal keel
Defs: The carina that is the median mesoscutal line.

label: median scapo-pedicellar muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises anterolaterally on the scape and inserts medially on the proximal part of the pedicel.

label: mesocoxal foramen
Defs: The coxal foramen that is on the mesopectus.

label: lateral metapleuro-second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metapleuron.

label: metapleuro-propodeal muscle
Defs: The propodeal muscle that arises from the metapleuron.

label: mandibular appendage
Defs: The area that is located proximoventrally on the mandible, is projected posteriorly and bears posteroventrally oriented rows of spines.

label: marginal rim of scutellum
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum and is delimited anteriorly by the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus.

label: median frontal septum
Defs: The ridge that is unpaired, vertical, is located in the dorsoventral midline of the frons and corresponds to the site of origin of the posterior fronto-labral muscles.

label: median tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises anteriorly from the anterior tentorial arm anteromedially of the site of origin of the anterior tentorio-scapal muscle and inserts medially on the proximal part of the scape.

label: intervolsellar process
Defs: The projection that is located distomedially on the parossiculus and is continuous with the volsellar ridge.

label: prespiracular carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the spiracular furrow medially.

label: prepecto-anterior thoracic spiracle muscle
Defs: The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that originates from the prepectus and inserts on the mesothoracic spiracle.

label: prepectal shelf
Defs: The area that is horizontal and located ventrally on the prepectus.

label: prepectal carina
Defs: The carina that divides the prepectus for the vertical lateral portion and the horizontal, ventral prepectal shelf.

label: prealare
Defs: na

label: prepecto-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the prepectus.

label: propleural arm-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleural arm.

label: propleural arm-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that originates from the propleural arm.

label: postscutellum
Defs: The area that is located medially on the dorsellum and bears the metanotal flange.

label: postoccipital carina
Defs: The rim that surrounds the occipital foramen.

label: occipital suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the malar sulcus and the occipital foramen.

label: posterior tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises medially from the proximal parts of the dorsal and anterior tentorial arms and is inserted posteriorly (dorsally) on the proximal part of the scape.

label: posterior T9-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises medially from the posterodorsal part of female T9 and inserts on the median bridge of the second valvifers.

label: posterior stipito-palpal muscle
Defs: The stipito-palpal muscle that arises medially on the proximal part of the stipes and inserts posteroproximally on the first maxillary palpal segment.

label: posterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises posteroventrally from the second valvifer and inserts on the processus musculares of the second valvula.

label: posterior scutellum
Defs: The area that is posterior and set of from the mesoscutellum by a transverse line.

label: posterior pronoto-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The pronoto-laterocervical muscle that originates from the pronotum posterior to the anterior pronoto-laterocervical muscle and inserts on the laterocervical apodeme.

label: posterior projection of mesoscutellum
Defs: The paired process that is located posteriorly on the dorsal surface of the mesoscutellum.

label: posterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the metanotum posterior to the site of origin of the anterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.

label: frontal lobe
Defs: The flange that is located on the frontal carina and obscures the antennal foramen.

label: frontal triangle
Defs: The area that is located between the epistomal sulcus and the frontal line .

label: frontofacial ridge
Defs: The line that delimits dorsally the scrobal depression.

label: frontovertex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the vertex and the dorsal area of the upper face dorsal to the frontofacial ridge.

label: transverse trabecula
Defs: The bar that extends between each eye ventral (anterior) to the anterior ocellus and dorsal (posterior) to the antennal formamina and laterally terminates at the juncture of the supraorbital trabecula and preorbital trabecula.

label: frontal line
Defs: The line that delimits dorsally the frontal triangle.

label: callus
Defs: The area that is located laterally of the propodeal spiracle and is delimited anterolaterally by the metapleural sulcus.

label: proctiger
Defs: The area that is located arond the anal opening posterior to the epipygium and hypopygium.

label: mediosternite 2
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: mediosternite 3
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 3.

label: mediosternite 4
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 4.

label: mediosternite 5
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: mediosternite 6
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 6.

label: mediosternite 7
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 7.

label: mediosternite 8
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 8.

label: mediosternite 9
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: mediosternite 10
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 10.

label: abdominal sternum 10
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 10.

label: laterosternite
Defs: The sternite that is located laterally on an abdominal sternum.

label: laterosternite 2
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: laterosternite 3
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 3.

label: laterosternite 5
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: laterosternite 6
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 6.

label: laterosternite 7
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 7.

label: laterosternite 8
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 8.

label: laterosternite 9
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: laterosternite 10
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 10.

label: laterosternite 4
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 4.

label: interscrobal surface
Defs: The area that is limited laterally by the antennal scrobes.

label: frontofacial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is transverse, located on the upper face and medially joining or intersecting the scrobal sulcus and interantennal area.

label: posterolateral tooth-like section of the anterior part of the pronotal plate
Defs: The projection that is located submedially on the proximal margin of the pronotal rim.

label: submedian pronotal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located submedially just ventrally of the dorsal margin of the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of the pronoto-propleural muscle.

label: antecostal sulcus of the first abdominal tergum
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the metaphragma.

label: ventral impressed area of metanotum
Defs: The area that is median and is delimited anteriorly by the metascutellar arms and the metascutelum.

label: dorsal plate
Defs: The sclerite that is paired, is located distal to the manubrium and is connected laterally with the arcus.

label: ventral spine of hypopygium
Defs: The area that is median and projecting posteriorly.

label: posterior carina of subaxillular bar
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the subaxillular bar.

label: mesotrochantellus
Defs: The trochantellus that is located on the mid femur.

label: metatrochantellus
Defs: The trochantellus that is located on the metafemur.

label: mediotergite
Defs: The area that is located medially on the tergum and is separated laterally by a line from the laterotergite.

label: laterotergite
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the tergum and is delimited by a longitudinal edge.

label: axillary cord of the hind wing
Defs: The axillary cord that is located on the hind wing.

label: axillary cord of the fore wing
Defs: The axillary cord that is located on the fore wing.

label: fifth tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the fourth tarsomere.

label: fourth tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the third tarsomere.

label: palpomere
Defs: The sclerite that is part of the palp.

label: second tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the basitarsus and proximal to the third tarsomere.

label: third tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the second tarsomere.

label: metapleuron
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is limited ventrally by the ventral carina of the metapleuron and dorsally by the metapleural carina.

label: transverse carina of T2
Defs: The carina that transversely crosses abdominal mediotergite 3 posterior to the antecostal sulcus.

label: mesepisternum
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the mesepimeral sulcus.

label: abdominal tergite 10
Defs: The tergite that is located on the abdominal tergum 10.

label: abdominal sternite 8
Defs: The sternite that is located on the abdominal sternum 8.

label: postspiracular furrow
Defs: The groove that is longitudinal and is immediately posterior or postero-medial to the first abdominal spiracle.

label: metapostnotum
Defs: The area that is located anterior to the antecostal sulcus of the first abdominal tergum.

label: median longitudinal carina of first metasomal sternum
Defs: The carina that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the first metasomal sternum.

label: median longitudinal carina of the metasomal tergum
Defs: The carina that is located in the nteroposterior median lineof the metasomal tergum.

label: median longitudinal furrow of mesoscutellum
Defs: The impression that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the mesoscutellum.

label: sublateral carina of tergum
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and sublateral.

label: transverse carina on S2
Defs: The carina that traverse the second abdominal sternum and separates a anterior vertical and a posterior horizontal petiolar area.

label: second flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the first flagellomere.

label: tenth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the ninth flagellomere.

label: fifth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the fourth flagellomere.

label: frontal ledge
Defs: The edge that traverses the upper face between the antennal foramen and the median ocellus separating a more horizontal dorsal and a more vertical ventral area.

label: transmetapectal carina
Defs: The carina that extends from the lateral metacoxal articulation and is continuous with the anterior margin of the speculum.

label: dorsal area of the metapectus
Defs: The area that is part of the metapectal-propodeal complex and is located ventral of the metapleural carina and dorsal of the transmetapectal carina.

label: stridulitrum
Defs: The area that is composed of file-like ridges on the upper surface of the anterior tergum of abdominal segment 4.

label: profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the profurca and inserts on the procoxa.

label: release and spread structure
Defs: The evaporatorium that is located on the sex segment.

label: third flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the second flagellomere.

label: fourth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the third flagellomere.

label: sixth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the fifth flagellomere.

label: seventh flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the sixth flagellomere.

label: eighth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the seventh flagellomere.

label: ninth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the eighth flagellomere.

label: eleventh flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the tenth flagellomere.

label: notaular ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds with the notaulus.

label: mesoscutellar arm
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum between the axillary level and the mesoscutellar disc, enclosing the anatomical space connecting the axillary level with the pulsatory organ of the fore wing.

label: acropleural ridge
Defs: The ridge that delimits anteriorly the acropleuron.

label: posterior rim of the propodeum
Defs: The rim that extends along the propodeal foramen.

label: profurcal bridge
Defs: The area that connects distally the lateral profurcal arms.

label: flexor apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located dorsally on the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex and corresponds to the site of origin of the metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of the hind wing muscle.

label: dorsal prepectal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the prepectus.

label: posterior prepectal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the prepectus.

label: anus
Defs: The anatomical space that is located between the hypoproct and the epiproct and is continuous with the alimentary canal.

label: transverse carina on T2
Defs: The carina that delimits the anterior vertical area of T2 from the posterior horizontal area.

label: mesoscutum length
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest among lines extending between the anterior and posterior margins of the mesoscutum.

label: pectal fossa of the coxa
Defs: The fossa that is located on the coxa and accommodates the coxal condyle of the pleuron.

label: coxal condyle of the pectus
Defs: The condyle that is located on the pectus and inserts into the pectal fossa of the coxa.

label: lateral propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that arises submedially from the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex, is longitudinal and extends towards the propodeal foramen.

label: inner orbit
Defs: The area that extends along the inner margin of the compound eye and is differentiated from the rest of the frons by different coloration.

label: Metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex
Defs: The sclerite that is connected anterolaterally and anteroventrally with the pronotum and anterodorsally with the mesoscutellum and the mesopostnotum.

label: visceral muscle
Defs: The muscle that is attached to the alimentary canal.

label: protarsal claw
Defs: The tarsal claw that is located in the fore leg.

label: mesotarsal claw
Defs: The tarsal claw that is located in the mid leg.

label: metatarsal claw
Defs: The tarsal claw that is located in the hind leg.

label: anterior extension of lateral axillar area
Defs: The area that is located anteroventrally on the lateral axillar area, accommodates the ventral part of the posterior extension of the preaxilla and bears the postmedian notal wing process.

label: central keel
Defs: The frontal line that is a carina.

label: transverse propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that is transverse and connects the metapleural carinae.

label: mucro
Defs: The projection that is median and is located anteriorly on the propodeum.

label: gastral scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is located ventrally of the propodeal foramen and accommodates the gaster.

label: lateral carina of the gastral scrobe
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the gastral scrobe.

label: interantennal area
Defs: The area that is delimited dorsally by the antennal scrobes.

label: longitudinal sensillum
Defs: The multiporous plate sensillum that is elongate.

label: remigium
Defs: The area that is located anterior to the claval furrow.

label: anterior cranio-mandibular articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the mandibular acetabulum and the pleurostomal condyle.

label: annulus of petiole
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly of the transverse carina of the petiole.

label: anterior metatibial spur
Defs: The spur that is located at the anterior edge of the metatibia.

label: calyptra
Defs: The flange that is located just laterally of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: circumscutellar carina
Defs: The carina that encompasses a horizontal, median, rounded area of the mesoscutellar disc.

label: facial impression
Defs: The area that is concave and is located between and ventral of the antennal foramina.

label: hairy ring of T3
Defs: The setiferous patch that is extending along the third metasomal tergum.

label: intertergal suture
Defs: The line of separation that is located between consecutive abdominal terga.

label: lateroventral mesopleural carina
Defs: The carina that extends lateroventrally on the mesopleuron between the lateral end of the epicnemium and the lateral margin of the mesocoxal foramen.

label: longitudinal scutellar carina
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends between the anterior and posterior margins of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex.

label: longitudinal ridge on the posterior surface of metatibia
Defs: The carina that extends along the posterior surface of the metatibia between the distal and proximal ends of the metatibia.

label: median carina of lower face
Defs: The carina that extends medially on the lower face.

label: median mesoscutal impression
Defs: The median mesoscutal line that is an impression.

label: mesopleural impression
Defs: The groove that corresponds to the transepisternal line.

label: metafemoral spine
Defs: The spine that is located on the anterior face of the metafemur.

label: metapleural cavity
Defs: The impression that is located at the anteroventral corner of the metapleuron.

label: metepimeron
Defs: The depression that is concave and is located at the anterior end of the metapleural sulcus.

label: pronotal crest
Defs: The flange that is located medially on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and overlaps the anterior part of the mesoscutum.

label: facial triangle
Defs: The area that is raised and  extends from between the antennal foramina to the posterior margin of the clypeus.

label: setal pit
Defs: The impression with a centered seta.

label: posteroventral cavity of female T7
Defs: The setal pit that is located at the posterior margin of abdominal tergum 8.

label: scutellar spine
Defs: The spine that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutellum.

label: transverse median carina on scutellar plate
Defs: The carina that extends transversely across the scutellar plate, anterior to glandular release pit.

label: ventral keel of petiole
Defs: The carina that is median and extends ventrally along the petiole.

label: occipital margin
Defs: The edge that separates the occiput from the vertex.

label: scutellar sensillum
Defs: The campaniform sensilla that is paired and is located submedially on the mesoscutellum.

label: campaniform sensillum
Defs: The aporous sensillum with a flat or dome-shaped, circular cuticular component that is delimited by a shallow depression.

label: secretory pore
Defs: The anatomical space that corresponds to the distal end of an exocrine gland.

label: specialized area of mesoscutellum
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutellum.

label: anterior propodeal projection
Defs: The projection that is located submedially on the anterior margin of the propodeum.

label: metasomal segment
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located in the metasoma.

label: thorax
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the pterothorax and the metapectus.

label: subantennal carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the lower face ventrally of the antennal foramen and dorsally of the clypeus.

label: medial tooth
Defs: The projection that is paired and is located submedially on the ventral margin of the ventral rim of clypeus.

label: lateral projection

label: posterior area of the second valvifer
