Defs: The sclerite that is located medially on the paraglossa and articulates with the anterior glossal plate and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod..

label: ventrolateral basiglossal arm
Defs: The projection that is located proximolaterally on the anterior glossal plate and articulates with the basiparaglossal sclerite.

label: median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate
Defs: The median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate that is parallel with the anteroposterior body axis.

label: glossal annulus
Defs: The anatomical cluster of the glossa that is composed of connected annular hairs.

label: annular hair
Defs: The spine on the distal part of ligula that is connected proximolaterally to the neighboring glossal hair by a carina.

label: distal glossal edge
Defs: The transverse edge that extends distally on the glossa.

label: posterior surface of the glossa
Defs: The area of the glossa that is between the distal margin of the prementum and the distal glossal edge.

label: anterior surface of the glossa
Defs: The area of the glossa that is between the distal glossal edge and the anterior glossal plate.

label: apical glossal hairs
Defs: The row of spines that is on the distal glossal edge.

label: apical glossal setae
Defs: The row of setae of the glossa that is adjacent to the distal glossal edge.

label: styloconic sensillum
Defs: The seta that is on a process.

label: campaniform sensillum of the glossa
Defs: The campaniform sensillum of the anterior surface of the glossa that is located proximal to the glossal annuli.

label: distal hypopharyngeal invagination
Defs: The invagination on the distal hypopharynx that id adjacent to the concavities of the hypopharyngeal rods.

label: hypopharyngeal pecten
Defs: The anterolateral area of the distal hypopharynx that is adjacent with the proximal part of the hypopharyngeal rod proximal to the hypopharyngeal button and is covered with acanthae.

label: anterolateral wall of the stipes
Defs: The area that extends between anterior margin of the median wall of the stipes and the lateral margin of the posterior wall of the stipes and the base of the mandible and the labrum.

label: marginal fringe of the stipes
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the spines on the distal margin of the distolateral portion of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: distomedial stipital flange
Defs: The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped by the premental carina and overlaps the lateral premental face.

label: proximomedial stipital flange
Defs: The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped distally by the distomedial stipital carina and overlaps the lateral premental face and the proximal part of the prementum.

label: cranial fossa of the cardo
Defs: The fossa that is located on the cardo and articulates with the cardinal condyle of the cranium.

label: fifth sclerite of the maxillary palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label: uniporous sensillum
Defs: The sensillum whose cuticular component has one cuticular pore.

label: fourth intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the third sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label: Stipital articular surface of the postmentum
Defs: The articular surface that articulates with the madial margin of the stipes.

label: median postmental ridge
Defs: The ridge that is limited laterally by the stipital articular surfaces of the postmentum.

label: postmento-premental hinge
Defs: The conjunctiva that is between the postmentum and prementum.

label: premental ditch
Defs: The scrobe of the prementum that is adjacent to and extends lateral to the premental carina and accommodates the medial part of the posterior stipital sclerite.

label: distal hypopharyngeal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that receives the site of insertions of the dorsal and ventral premento-salivarial muscles and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod.

label: ventral glossal lines
Defs: The carinae that radiates from the posterior glossal plate towards the apical glossal setae.

label: basal glossal invagination
Defs: The anterior invagination of the labium that is adjacent with the distal end of the salivarium and separates the glossa proximally from the distal hypopharynx and the paraglossae.

label: paraglossal acroglossal button
Defs: The sclerite that is located distally on the paraglossa.

label: paraglossal annulus
Defs: The anatomical cluster of the paraglossa that is composed of connected annular hairs.

label: hypopharyngeal button
Defs: The bent area of the hypopharyngeal rod that receives the site of insertion of the posterior tentorio-premental muscle.

label: salivary gland
Defs: The gland that empties anterior to the prementum.

label: first intrinsic muscle of the labial palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the first sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the second sclerite of the labial palp.

label: second intrinsic muscle of the labial palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the second sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the labial palp.

label: posteroventral corner of the first valvifer
Defs: The corner of the first valvifer that is adjacent to the intervalvifer articulation.

label: length of anterior area of second valvifer
Defs: The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical lines that extend between the anterior and posterior margins of the anterior area of the second valvifer.

label: length of female T9
Defs: The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical lines that extend between the anterior and posterior margins of female T9.

label: mandibular dentition
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the mandibular teeth.

label: galeal comb
Defs: The row of setae that is located on the medial wall of the galeo-lacinial complex proximal to the coeloconic sensilla of galea.

label: campaniform sensillum of the premenum
Defs: The campaniform sensillum that is on the ventral premental face.

label: distolateral premental incision
Defs: The concavity on the distal margin of the prementum delimiting medially the site of attachment of the labial palp.

label: labial palpomere
Defs: The sclerite that is part of the labial palp.

label: glossal styloconic sensillum
Defs: The styloconic sensillum that is located apically on the glossa.

label: medial apodeme of female S7
Defs: The apophysis that is located proximomedially on the female S7.

label: tubular A9
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the female T8 with female T9 and is tubular.

label: metapleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the ridge that is continuous with the third phragma and extends between the metapleural apodeme.

label: mesosoma height
Defs: na

label: posterior tooth of the mandible
Defs: The tooth tooth that is located on the posterior surface of the lower tooth.

label: clypeo-compound eye distance
Defs: The distance that is the shortest between the compound eye and the anterior tentorial pit and the compound eye.

label: eye height
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest vertical diameter of the compound eye in frontal view.

label: cranial scrobe of mesoscutum
Defs: The scrobe on the mesonotum that accommodates the posterior surface of the cranium.

label: scrobal carina of the mesoscutum
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the cranial scrobe of the mesoscutum.

label: metanoto-metapectal-propodeal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends between the metanotum and the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: profemoral scrobe of the mesopectus
Defs: The scrobe that is on the mesopectus and accommodates the profemur.

label: dorsolateral setal patch of propodeum
Defs: The setal patch that is elongate, is adjacent and extends just lateral to the plica and is composed of posteriorly directed and apressed setae that inserts into the retinaculum when the fore wing is in a flexed position.

label: anterodistal notch of the fore wing
Defs: The notch that is on the anterior wing margin, is adacent to the anterior end of the poststigmal fold line.

label: posterodistal notch of the fore wing
Defs: The notch on the posterior wing margin that is adjacent to the posterior end of the discal fold.

label: petiole length
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the transverse carina on petiole and the posterior margin of the petiole.

label: median anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends in the median axis of the organism.

label: epistomal distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the anterior tentorial pits.

label: anterolateral mesopectal projection
Defs: The projection that is located anterolaterally on the epicnemial carina.

label: petiolar scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is located ventrally of the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximal area of the petiole.

label: lateroventral carina of the petiole
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends lateroventrally on the abdominal segment 2.

label: median conjunctiva of abdominal tergum 9
Defs: The conjunctiva of abdominal tergum 9 that is median and longitudinal.

label: head width
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest horizontal diameter of the cranium in frontal view.

label: facet
Defs: The portion of cuticle that covers externally the cellular components of the ommatidium.

label: ventral margin of the mesopectus
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the acetabular carina and the medial coxal articulations.

label: ventral margin of the metapectus
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the anterior margin of the ventral region of the metapectus and the distal end of the projection bearing the medial coxal condyle of the metapectus.

label: proximodistal anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the proximal and distal margins of an anatomical structure.

label: head+mesosoma length
Defs: na

label: head+mesosoma length
Defs: The median anatomical line that is the longest between the anterior margin of the head and the propodeal foramen in dorsal view.

label: mesosoma height
Defs: The anatomical line that is parallel with the posterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex, is adjacent to the anterior margin of the mesocoxa and extends between the dorsal and ventral margins of the mesosoma.

label: posterior mesoscutellar area
Defs: The area delimited by the posterior mesoscutellar carina and by the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: posterior mesoscutellar carina
Defs: The carina on the posterior face of the mesoscutellum that is dorsally convex.

label: posterolateral mesoscutellar area
Defs: The area delimited by the posterolateral mesoscutellar carina and the ventral margin of the mesoscutellum

label: posterolateral mesoscutellar carina
Defs: The carina on the posterodorsal mesoscutellum that is dorsally convex.

label: anterior part of pronotal plate
Defs: The area medially on the anterior rim of the pronotum that is distinctly delineated and its outline directly continuous with the scutellar foveae and the pronotal plate.

label: anteroventral depression of pronotum
Defs: The groove along the anteroventral border of the pronotum.

label: anteroventral foramen of metapleuron
Defs: The anatomical space delimited by a notch on the margin of the metapleuron in its anteroventral corner, opening towards a depression in the anterior part of the metasubpleuron.

label: scutellar rim
Defs: Tha carina that extends externally of the scutellar plate and is parallel to the margin of the scutellar plate.

label: dorsal rim of pronotal plate
Defs: The carina that extends along the posterior border of the pronotal plate.

label: pronotal fovea
Defs: The well delineated depressed area that is submedian on the pronotum, and is delimited medially by the median bridge of the pronotal plate.

label: median septum of scutellum
Defs: The area that is median and separates the scutellar foveae.

label: ovipositor clip
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the distal notch on the second valvula and the associated dentition and flexible flap.

label: posterior lobe of scutellum
Defs: The part of the mesoscutellum that protrudes posteriorly as a distinct shape beyond any smooth or straight posterior outline, especially when protruding posteriorly past the anterior margin of the metanotum

label: posterior part of pronotal plate
Defs: The area of the pronotal plate that is posterior to the pronotal foveae.

label: subcalyptral area
Defs: The area of the propodeum that is  delimited dorsally by the calyptra and posteriorly delimited by the lateral propodeal carina.

label: window under lateral bar
Defs: The anatomical space that is encircled by the lateral bar of the mesoscutellum.

label: posteroventral corner of metapleuron
Defs: The corner at the intersection of the ventrolateral and posterior margin of the metapleuron.

label: pronoto-mesoscutal suture
Defs: The line of separation between the pronotum and the mesoscutum.

label: pronoto-mesopectal suture
Defs: The line of separation between the pronotum and the mesopectus.

label: mesopleural line
Defs: The straight line that extends ventrally on the lateral (vertical) surface of the mesopectus and is oriented anteroposteriorly.

label: metapleuron
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is anterior to the metapleural carina and lateral to the metadiscrimen.

label: sensillum basiconicum
Defs: The trichoid sensillum that is apically rounded.

label: lateral clypeal seta
Defs: The seta that is located laterally on the clypeus.

label: large volcano sensilla
Defs: The sensillum with a distal, volcano-shape cuticular component on the apical-most flagellomere.

label: large disc sensilla
Defs: The row of sensilla whose cuticular component are flat, circular and lack a median peg.

label: sensillum coeloconicum A
Defs: The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is 1/3-1/5 of the diameter of the surrounding depression.

label: sensillum coeloconicum B
Defs: The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is as wide as the surrounding depression.

label: axillar crescent
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of the transaxillar carina, axillar carina, and axillular carina.

label: width
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

label: mesosoma length
Defs: The anatomical line that connects the global minima of the contour line of the pronotal slope in lateral view when the specimen is rotated until the contour line becames as symmetric as possible and the posteriormost point of the propodeal lobe.

label: anterior petiolar length
Defs: The median anatomical line between the setal line of petiole and the transverse carina of petiole.

label: anterior pronotal slope
Defs: The concave area anteriorly on the mesosoma that accommodates the posterior area of the cranium.

label: anterior setal pit
Defs: The anteriormost setal pit on the dorsal side of the petiole.

label: dorsal petiolar scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is dorsal to the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximodorsal area of the petiole.

label: dorsal head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and dorsal head line in frontal view.

label: dorsal head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the posteriormost (dorsalmost) points of compound eyes in frontal view.

label: distal clypeal line
Defs: The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the median anatomical line and is the tangent at the distalmost point(s) of the clypeus in frontal view.

label: diagonal petiolar length
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the distalmost point of the subpetiolar process and the global minima of the contour line of the dorsal region of the posterior petiolar constriction in lateral view when the specimen is rotated until the contour line became as symmetric as possible.

label: caudal cylinder
Defs: The petiolar area posterior to the posterior petiolar constriction.

label: apical spine distance
Defs: The anatomical line between the distal ends of the propodeal spines.

label: external area of the scape
Defs: The area of the scape that faces away from the cranial surface in fully caudal scape position.

label: facial area of the scape
Defs: The area of the scape that faces the cranium surface when the scape is in fully flexed position.

label: transverse torular line
Defs: The anatomical line that is tangential to the posteriormost points of the antennal rims.

label: frontal carina line
Defs: The transverse torular line that extends between the frontal carinae.

label: lateral carina of clypeus
Defs: The carina that extends between the ventral (anterior) margin of the antennal foramen to the apical clypeal margin.

label: maximum cephalic length
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal clypeal line in frontal view.

label: maximum diameter of the compound eye
Defs: The longest diameter of the eye.

label: maximum height of petiolar node
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest between the dorsal margin of the petiole and the posterior petiolar distance and perpendicular to the posterior petiolar distance.

label: maximum petiole height
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest between the ventral margin of the petiole and the dorsal margin of the petiole and is perpendicular to the ventral margin of the petiole in lateral view.

label: angle
Defs: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement at an angle.

label: setal angle
Defs: The angle of the proximodistal axis of the seta to the contour line of the bodypart where the seta is located.

label: maximum cephalic length in median line
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal margin of the clypeus in frontal view.

label: median clypeal notch
Defs: The median notch that is on the distal clypeal margin.

label: median clypeal notch depth
Defs: The anatomical line that is between the distal clypeal line and the proximalmost point of the distal clypeal notch in frontal view.

label: Maximum spiracle distance of propodeum
Defs: The anatomical line that connects the center of the propodeal spiracle with the posteriormost point of the propodeal lobe in lateral view.

label: pronotum width
Defs: The longest width of the pronotum in dorsal view.

label: length of petiolar node
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the center of the petiolar spiracle and the posterior margin of the petiole in lateral view.

label: anterodorsal spine of the petiolar node
Defs: The anterolateral spine of the dorsal side of the petiolar node.

label: apical petiolar spine distance
Defs: The anatomical line between the distal ends of the anterodorsal spines of the petiolar node.

label: petiole width
Defs: The maximum width of the petiole in dorsal view.

label: postocular distance
Defs: The median anatomical line of the cranium that is the longest between the dorsal margin of the cranium and the dorsal head width.

label: postpetiole length
Defs: The longest anatomical line that is perpendicular to the posterior margin of the postpetiole in lateral view and is between the posterior postpetiolar margin and the anterior postpetiolar margin.

label: postpetiole width
Defs: The maximum width of the postpetiole in dorsal view.

label: cranial scrobe of the pronotum
Defs: The scrobe on the pronotum that accommodates the posterior surface of the cranium.

label: pronotal spine
Defs: The spine that is located at the dorsolateral edge of the cranial scrobe of the pronotum.

label: apical distance of pronotal spines
Defs: The anatomical line between the distal ends of the pronotal spines.

label: scape length
Defs: The proximodistal anatomical line of the scapal area that is distal to the radicle.

label: minimum spine distance
Defs: The shortest anatomical line between the lateral margins of the propodeal spines.

label: spine length
Defs: The anatomical line between the center of the propodeal spiracle and the distal end of the propodeal spine.

label: arithmetic mean
Defs: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

label: absolute cephalic size
Defs: The arithmetic mean of the maximum cephalic length in median line and the dorsal head width.

label: anterodorsal rim of petiole
Defs: The rim that is transverse and is at the posterior margin of the anterior profile of petiolar node.

label: circumantennal carinae
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of concentric carinae that encircle the antennal foramen.

label: anterior profile of petiolar node
Defs: The anteriodorsal area of the petiolar node that is oriented anterodorsally and is delimited posteriorly by a dorsally or posterodorsally orineted area.

label: dorsal petiolar profile
Defs: The area of the petiolar node that is dorsomedial, and oriented dorsally and is delimited anteriorly by the anterior petiolar profile and posteriorly by the caudal petiolar profile.

label: caudal petiolar profile
Defs: The area of the petiolar node that is posterodorsal, oriented posterodorsally and is delimited anteriorly by a dorsally or anterodorsally oriented area.

label: portion of epithelium
Defs: The anatomical structure of the epithelium that is delimited by material or immaterial anatomical entities.

label: postocular area
Defs: The area of the cranium between the dorsal margin of the compound eye and the posterolateral cranial corner.

label: postocular contour line
Defs: The contour line of the postocular area in frontal view.

label: postocular head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the posteriormost points of the postocular contour lines.

label: metapleural area of the mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex
Defs: The lateral (vertical) area that is posterior to the mesometapleural sulcus and anterior to the metapleural carina.

label: mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex
Defs: The sclerite that is connected to the pronotum, propleura, fore, middle and hind legs and the petiole via conjunctiva.

label: metanotal depression
Defs: The transverse, dorsal groove on the mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex posterior to the pronotal spiracle and anterior to the propodeal spiracle.

label: mesopleural area of the mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex
Defs: The lateral (vertical) area that is anterior to the mesometapleural sulcus and posterior to the pronotum.

label: median carina of clypeus
Defs: The clypeal carina that is median.

label: submedian area of clypeus
Defs: The area between the median carina of clypeus and the lateral carina of clypeus.

label: ventral head line
Defs: The anatomical line between the anteriormost (ventralmost) points of compound eyes in frontal view.

label: torular head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and transverse torular line line in frontal view. dorsal head width

label: ventral head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and ventral head line in frontal view. dorsal head width

label: contour line
Defs: The boundary of the orthographic projection of a defined side of the anatomical structure.

label: gena contour line
Defs: The contour line of the gena area in frontal view.

label: anterior profile of petiolar node contour line
Defs: The contour line of the anterior profile of petiolar node in lateral view.

label: dorsal petiolar profile contour line
Defs: The contour line of the dorsal petiolar profile in lateral view.

label: malar striae
Defs: The anatomical cluster posterior to the malar sulcus that is composed of carinae radiating from the pleurostomal condyle.

label: pleural pit line
Defs: The anatomical line between the mesopleural and metapleural pits.

label: width
Defs: The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the anatomical structure and between one side of an object to the opposite side.

label: facial striae
Defs: The anatomical cluster anterior to the malar sulcus that is composed of carinae radiating from the pleurostomal condyle.

label: maximum width
Defs: The width that is the longest.

label: minimum width
Defs: The width that is the shortest.

label: reticulate
Defs: The sculpture that is composed of scutes.

label: supraclypeal depression
Defs: The median impression on the frons that is dorsal to the intertorular carina and is not a scrobe for receiving the scape.

label: ventromedian setiferous patch
Defs: The median setiferous patch that is on the frons between the intertorular carina and the facial pit.

label: ventrolateral setiferous patch
Defs: The sublateral setiferous patch that is on the frons between the intertorular carina and the facial pit, and is separated from the median setiferous patch by the supraclypeal depression.

label: intertorular area
Defs: The median area of the face between the dorsal (posterior) margin of the clypeus and the intertolural carina.

label: facial process
Defs: The process that is located on the upper face dorsal to the intertorular carina and corresponds internally to a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

label: postocellar carina
Defs: The carina that connects the posterior margins of the left and right lateral ocellar fovea.

label: distal projection of the parossiculus
Defs: The distal projection of the volsella that corresponds to the apical parossiculal seta.

label: facial apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is dorsal to the intertorular line and ventral to the anterior ocellus.

label: median facial keel
Defs: The carina whose dorsal (posterior) region overlaps the facial pit.

label: median flange of occipital carina
Defs: The flange that is median and on the occipital carina.

label: submedial flange of occipital carina
Defs: The flange that is submedial and is on the occipital carina.

label: distal projection of the penisvalva
Defs: The projection that is at the distal end of the penisvalva.

label: sensillar ring of harpe
Defs: The row of setae on the distomedial harpal wall that is parallel to the harpal margin.

label: anterior discrimenal pit
Defs: The pit at the anteriormost point of the mesodiscrimen.

label: proximolateral projection of the cupula
Defs: The projection that is between the proximodorsal notch of cupula and the proximoventral notch of the cupula.

label: proximoventral notch of cupula
Defs: The notch on the proximoventral margin of the cupula just lateral to the gonocondyle.

label: transverse line of the metanotum/propodeum
Defs: The line of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex that connects the humeral sclerite to the third phragma.

label: anteromedian projection of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex
Defs: The median projection on the anterior region of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex.

label: transverse frontal carina
Defs: The transverse carina that is dorsal to the facial pit and ventral to the anterior ocellus.

label: torulo-clypeal carina
Defs: The carina that is connects the clypeus with the antennal rim.

label: subtorular carina
Defs: The carina that extends ventrally from the lateral margin of the antennal rim.

label: ventrolateral invagination of the pronotum
Defs: The invagination that at the ventrolateral edge of the pronotum.

label: sternaulus length
Defs: The straight anatomical line between the anterior and posterior ends of the sternaulus.

label: mesopleuron length
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the lateral end of the epicnemial carina and the postpectal carina and is parallel to the lateroventral mesopleural carina.

label: anterior mesoscutal width

label: posterior mesoscutal width
Defs: The anatomical line that is between the anterior margins of the left and right preaxillae.

label: harpe width
Defs: The width of the harpe in lateral view.

label: head height

label: head length

label: harpe length
Defs: The anatomical line between the distalmost point of the gonostyle volsella complex and the distalmost point of the harpe in lateral view.

label: axillary muscle
Defs: The muscle that is attached to the axillary sclerite.

label: petiole neck
Defs: The anterior area of the petiole that is narrower than the posterior region in dorsal view.

label: buccal lobe
Defs: The area of the epipharyngeal wall that is posterior to the epipharyngeal lobe, is thicker than surrounding regions of the epipharyngeal wall and is covered with dorsally oriented acanthae.

label: body length
Defs: The anatomical line between the anteriormost pont of the cranium and the posteriormost point of the metasoma.

label: distoventral submedian corner of the cupula
Defs: The submedial corner at the distoventral margin of the cupula.

label: trachea
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is tubular, branched into tracheoles and bears the taenidia.

label: atrium
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is sclerotized and is between the external aperture of the spiracle and the distal end of the trachea.

label: resilin rich articulation of the ramus
Defs: The resilin rich area that is ringlike and connects the ramus with the rest of the flagellomere.

label: posteromedian process of the mesoscutellum
Defs: The median spine that is on the posterodorsal region of the mesoscutellum.

label: sensillar plate of the aedeagus
Defs: The distal region of the aedeagus that is flat (delimited by an edge from the rest of the aedeagus) and bears four sensillum basiconicum.

label: metapecto-propodeal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the lateral end of the antecostal sulcus of the first abdominal tergum with the anterior margin of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex.

label: posterodorsal metapleural area
Defs: The area that is anterior to the metapecto-propodeal conjunctiva, posterior to the metapleural pit and dorsal to the metapleural sulcus.

label: odontoid process
Defs: The flange that is located on the ventral edge of the mandible and not continuous with the mandibular condyle.

label: specillum
Defs: The median, smooth area that is smooth, is surrounded by sculptured areas and is on the abdominal mediotergite 4.

label: twelfth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the eleventh flagellomere.

label: axillular spine
Defs: The spine on the distal margin of the axillula.

label: anterior ocellar-orbital line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest among the lines that connect the internal margin of the compound eyes and are tangential to the anteriormost point on the median ocellus.

label: apical setae of T3
Defs: The row of setae that is transverse and located distally on the third metasomal mediotergite and is composed of setae at least 2 times as long as other setae on the metasoma.

label: stigmal vein
Defs: The vein that is adjacent proximally to the pterostigma.

label: postpetiole height
Defs: The maximum distance between the dorsal and ventral margin of the postpetiole in lateral view.

label: scute
Defs: The area that is 535 m wide, polygonal, repetitive, is delimited by lines and is the element of the reticulate sculpture.

label: lateral mesosoma length
Defs: The anatomical line between the anteriormost point of the anterior rim of pronotum and the posterodorsal edge of the nucha in lateral view.

label: transverse carina of the metasomal depression
Defs: The carina that is transverse and dorsal to the nucha.

label: coriaceous
Defs: The reticulate that is composed of convex scutes.

label: alutaceous
Defs: The reticulate that is composed of flat scutes.

label: dorsomedian area of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The dorsomedian area of the mesoscutellar axillar complex including the scutellar fovea and the mesoscutellar disc.

label: prepalpal ventral premental area
Defs: The area that is anterior to the anatomical line connecting the left and right labial palpal excisions.

label: postpalpal ventral premental area
Defs: The area that is posterior to the anatomical line connecting the left and right labial palpal excisions.

label: latero-proximal stipital process
Defs: The projection that is on the proximolateral margin of the posterior stipital sclerite.

label: cranial condyle of cardo
Defs: The condyle of the cardo that inserts into the cardinal condyle of the cranium and is adjacent to the cranial fossa of the cardo.

label: Distal lateral projection of cardo
Defs: The corner that is located laterally on the distal margin of the cardo.

label: Distal mesal projection of cardo
Defs: The corner that is located medially on the distal margin of the cardo.

label: lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes
Defs: The flange on the lateral part of the prinicipal carina of the stipes.

label: distal lobe of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes
Defs: The area of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes distal to the notch of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: proximal lobe of lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes
Defs: The area of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes proximal to the notch of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: lateral galeal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located laterally on the lateral wall of the galeo-lacinial complex.

label: trichoid sensillum of the glossa
Defs: The trichoid sensillum that is on the posterior surface of the glossa.

label: campaniform stipital sensillum
Defs: The campaniform sensillum on the stipes.

label: triangular mesopleural furrow
Defs: The ventrolateral, triangular impression adjacent posteriorly to the acetabular carina.

label: anteroposterior anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the anterior and posterior margins of an anatomical structure.

label: eye-torulus distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest distance between the compound eye and the torulus.

label: thirteenth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the twelfth flagellomere.

label: maximum diameter
Defs: The diameter that is the longest.

label: minimum diameter
Defs: The diameter that is the shortest.

label: microtrichia
Defs: The acantha that is on the wing blade.

label: maximum height
Defs: The height that is the longest.

label: posterodorsal metapleural sulcus
Defs: The groove on the posterodorsal margin of the metapleuron.

label: subacropleural sulcus
Defs: The groove ventral to the acropleural sulcus and anterior to the prespecular sulcus that extends toward the mesopleural pit.

label: postepomial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus along the dorsal margin of the transverse pronotal carina that is posterior to the epomial carina and ventral to the pronotal suprahumeral sulcus

label: anterior mesepisternal area
Defs: The area delimited anteriorly by the pronotal-mesopectal suture, posterodorsally by the ventral limit of the subacropleural sulcus, and posteroventrally by the episternal foveal line.

label: dorsal length of pronotum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the pronotum in dorsal view.

label: length of mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The median anatomical line of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex in dorsal view.

label: length of metanotum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the metanotum in dorsal view.

label: dorsal length of propodeum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the metapectal-propodeal complex in dorsal view.

label: length of 1st flagellomere
Defs: The proximodistal anatomical line of the 1st flagellomere.

label: width of 1st flagellomere
Defs: The width of the 1st flagellomere.

label: width of pedicel
Defs: The maximum width of the pedicel.

label: lateral eye height
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest vertical diameter of the compound eye in lateral view.

label: length of malar sulcus
Defs: The straight anatomical line between the proximal and distal ends of the malar sulcus.

label: lateral head length
Defs: The anatomical line that connects the widest point between the apical edge of the compound eyes and extends to the anterior and posterior cranial margins in lateral view.

label: dorsal length of mesoscutum
Defs: The mesoscutum length in dorsal view.

label: width of mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The maximum width of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex in dorsal view.

label: propodeal spiracle-metanotum distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the first abdominal spiracle and the lateral margin of the metanotum.

label: diameter of propodeal spiracle
Defs: The maximum diameter of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: length of T1
Defs: The median anatomical line of the abdominal tergum 2.

label: length of hypopygium
Defs: The median anatomical line of the hypopygium in ventral view.

label: T7+8
Defs: The distal region of the female abdomen whose posterior portion bears the cerci and the anterior portion is part of female T9.

label: prospinasterno-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the prorspinasternum.

label: metanoto-metalaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The metalaterophragmal muscle that arises from the metanotum.

label: corpotendon
Defs: The anteromedian apodeme on the tentorial bridge that receives the posterior contractor of the pharynx.

label: mola
Defs: The proximomedial region of the mandible that is adjacent to the mola of the opposite mandible and serves as a grinding surface.

label: mandibular rod
Defs: The sclerotised invaginations that are tubular and are inside the mandible.

label: apical peg
Defs: The peg-shaped sensillum that is apical on the apicalmost sclerite of the labial palp.

label: hind wing tegula
Defs: The tegula of the hind wing.

label: lateral incision of metanoum
Defs: The conjunctiva that is between the anterior and posterior metanotal wing processes.

label: cup-shaped apodeme of metabasalare
Defs: The apodeme that is cup shaped and recieves the site of insertion of the metabasalar muscles.

label: articular inflection
Defs: The fossa that receives the metepimeral condyle of abdomina tergum 1.

label: posterior paracoxal ridge
Defs: The paracoxal ridge that is posterior to the site of origin of the posterior metapleuro-metabasalar muscle.

label: metapectal plate
Defs: The flange that is on the paracoxal ridge and that serves as the site of attachment for the the anterior metapleuro-metabasalar and median metapleuro-metacoxal muscles.

label: articular notch
Defs: The notch at the base of the lateral coxal condyle of the metapleuron.

label: anterior metafurcal arm
Defs: The apodeme that is located anteromedially on the lateral metafurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral metafurco-mesofurcal muscle.

label: sturdy spines of the hind femur
Defs: The spine that is located on the ventral face of the metafemur.

label: preapical tibial spurs
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the spurs that are proximal to the distal margin of the tibia.

label: median antecostal projection
Defs: The projection that extends over the median portion of the antecostal sulcus.

label: lateral antecostal projection
Defs: The projection that extends over the lateral portion of the antecostal sulcus.

label: metalaterophragmal lobe
Defs: The flange of the metalaterophragma that is lateral and serves as the site of origin of the ph3-T2 muscle.

label: T2 longitudinal internal ridge
Defs: The longitudinal ridge of the petiole that is median.

label: abdominal segment 2-abdominal segment 1 articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the articular surfaces of abdominal segment 1 and abdominal segment 2.

label: furcula
Defs: The sclerite that is proximal to the second valvifer and receives the site of origin of the posterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.

label: meconium
Defs: The acellular anatomical structure that is in the hind gut of the pupa.

label: prothoracic katepisternum
Defs: The sclerite that is between the propleuron and the procoxa. The intrinsic muscle of the propleuron inserts on the conjunctiva anterior to the prothoracic katepisternum.

label: laterosternal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is between the procoxa and the prosternum.

label: transscutal ridge
Defs: The ridge that is adjacent posteriorly to the transscutal articulation.

label: internal median longitudinal scutoscutellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that is median and is at the posterior region of the mesoscutellum.

label: internal septum
Defs: The flange that extends along the margin of the mesoscutellum reducing its opening into the lumen of the mesoscutellum.

label: basalar apodeme
Defs: The cup-shaped, sclerotised region et the apical portion of the tendon of the basalare that serves as the site of origin of the basalare muscles.

label: supramesopleural sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located anterodorsally on the metapectus, posterior to the postalar process.

label: prospinasternal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme on the anteroventral margin of the mesopectus that serves as the site of origin of prospinasternal muscles.

label: mesospinasternal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is oriented poseteriorly and arises from the mesodiscrimenal lamella at the base of the mesofurca.

label: metepisternal anapleural cleft
Defs: The notch on the anterior margin of the metapectus just ventrally of the metapleural arm.

label: paracoxal notch
Defs: The notch that is at the lateral end of the paracoxal sulcus.

label: nygma
Defs: The sclerotized, round patch in the middle of wing cell.

label: anterior metapleural carina
Defs: The carina that is parallel to and extends anteroventrally of the metapleural carina, is continuous with the metapleural apodeme and is separated from the metapleural carina by a crenulate impresion

label: basal longitudinal carinae of the syntergum
Defs: The anteroposteriorly oriented carinae that arise posteriorly from the transverse carina on petiole.

label: flagellar scrobe of scape
Defs: The scrobe on the ventral region of the scape that accommodates the flagellum when it is pressed against the scape.

label: median conjunctiva of cardines
Defs: The conjunctiva that separates the left and the right cardines.

label: mesoscutellar comb
Defs: The median row of spines on the mesoscutellum.

label: mesonotal fossa of the pronotum
Defs: The submedian fossa that is located on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and accommodates the pronotal condyle of the mesonotum.

label: pronotal condyle of the mesoscutum
Defs: The submedial condyle that is located on the ventral margin of the mesoscutum and inserts into the mesonotal fossa of the pronotum.

label: pronoto-mesonotal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the pronotal condyle of the mesoscutum and the mesonotal fossa of the pronotum.

label: posterior mesosomal comb
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the posterolateral edge of the metanoto-propodeo-mesopecto-metapectal complex and the metacoxa.

label: posterodorsal branch of pronotal Y
Defs: The sulcus that connects the transverse pronotal sulcus and the posterior margin of the pronotum ventral to the anterior thoracic spiracle and together with the ventral portion of the transverse pronotal sulcus delimits anteriorly the site of origin of the pronoto-mesobasalar muscle.

label: proximodorsal apodeme of cupula
Defs: The median apodeme on the proximodorsal region of the cupula.

label: Proximodorsal inflection of cupulal margin
Defs: The median area at the  proximodorsal cupulal margin that is inflected and serves as the site of origin of the  dorsomedial cupulo-gonostipal muscles.

label: proximodorsal projection of harpe
Defs: The median projection on the proximodorsal region of the harpe that accommodates tha gonossiculus when it is pressed against the harpe.

label: Proximomedial brush of the harpe
Defs: The setiferous patch on the medial surface of the harpe.

label: transverse row of setae of cercus
Defs: The row of setae that is transverse and delimits the distal cercal area on T9.

label: Ventral invagination of mesometapleural sulcus
Defs: The invagination that is at the ventral end of the of the mesometapleural sulcus.

label: ventral invagination of the metapleural carina
Defs: The invagination that is at the ventral end of the of the metapleural carina.

label: clypeus-torulus distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the ventral margin of the torulus and the epistomal sulcus.

label: anterior ocellus-torulus distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortset between the ventral margin of the anterior ocellus and the dorsal margin of the torulus.

label: sixth maxillary palpal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected via conjunctiva distally to the fifth sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label: horizontal plate
Defs: The flange that extends dorsolaterally from the mesodiscrimenal lamella.
